<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt 0pt 0; color: #0066CC; text-indent: 36pt"><B>Friday, June 6, 2014</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 3pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 16pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt 0pt 0; text-indent: 36pt"><B>7:00 a.m., Central time</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 3pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify"><I>Bud Walton
Arena, University of Arkansas Campus, Fayetteville, Arkansas 72701</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify">We are pleased to invite you to join our Board of Directors, senior
leadership, and other shareholders for the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting of Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. The meeting will be
held on Friday, June 6, 2014, at 7:00 a.m., Central time in Bud Walton Arena on the campus of the University of Arkansas, Fayetteville,
Arkansas 72701. The purposes of the meeting are:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 86%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 36pt">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 15pt; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">1.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">to elect as directors the 14 nominees identified in the accompanying proxy statement;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">2.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">to ratify the appointment of Ernst &amp; Young LLP as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants for the fiscal&nbsp;year&nbsp;ending January 31, 2015;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">3.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">to vote on a non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s named executive officers as disclosed in the accompanying proxy statement;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">4.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">to vote on the three shareholder proposals described in the accompanying proxy statement, if properly presented at the meeting; and </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">5.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">to transact any other business properly brought before the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B><I>&nbsp;</I></B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify"><B><I>The Board of Directors set April 11, 2014 as the record
date for the meeting. This means that only shareholders of record of Walmart as of the close of business on that date are entitled
to:</I></B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 86%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 36pt">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">receive this notice of the meeting; and</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">vote at the meeting and any adjournments or postponements of the meeting.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify"><B><I>Attending the Meeting in Person.
</I></B>If you plan to attend the meeting in person, please see page 88 for information regarding what you must bring with you
to gain admittance to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify"><B><I>Your Vote is Important to Us.</I>
</B>Regardless of whether you plan to attend, we urge all shareholders to vote on the matters described in the accompanying proxy
statement. Please see pages 85-86 for information about voting by mail, telephone, the internet, mobile device, or in person at
the 2014&nbsp;Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Voting by proxy in any of the ways described will not prevent you from attending
the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt; text-align: justify">The proxy statement and our Annual Report
to Shareholders for the fiscal year ended January 31, 2014 are available in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo; section of our corporate
website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 36pt"><B>April 23, 2014</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 3pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 36pt">Bentonville, Arkansas</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt 0pt 0; text-align: right">By Order of the Board of Directors</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 36pt 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmtx3x2.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;</P>

<div style="border:#0066CC 1px solid; width:99%; padding:5pt">
<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0;"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta002"></A>Proxy Statement
Summary</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>You have received these proxy materials
because the Board is soliciting your proxy to vote your Shares at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. This summary highlights
information contained elsewhere in this proxy statement. This summary does not contain all of the information that you should consider,
and you should read the entire proxy statement carefully before voting. Page references (&ldquo;XX&rdquo;) are supplied to help
you find further information in this proxy statement. Please refer to the Table of Abbreviations on page 90 for the meaning of
certain terms used in this proxy summary and the rest of this proxy statement. This proxy statement and the related proxy materials
were first mailed to shareholders and made available on the internet on April 23, 2014.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting</B></FONT></P>



<P STYLE="margin: 0; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"></P>

<P STYLE="text-align: justify; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><B>Date and Time: </B>June 6, 2014, 7:00 a.m., Central time<B></B></P>

<P STYLE="text-align: justify; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="text-align: justify; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><B>Place: </B>Bud Walton Arena, University of Arkansas Campus, Fayetteville, Arkansas 72701</P>

<P STYLE="text-align: justify; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="text-align: justify; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 6pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify"><B>Record Date: </B>You can vote if you were a shareholder of record of the company at the close of business on April 11, 2014 (page 83).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify"><B>Admission: </B>You must have proof of ownership of Shares as of the record date above to attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting (page 88).</P>


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If you are unable to attend in person, you
can view a live webcast of the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports</I>.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Voting Matters
and Board Recommendations</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Board is not aware of any matter that
will be presented for a vote at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting other than those shown above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>How to Cast
Your Vote (pages 85-86)</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">You can vote by any of the following methods:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">via the internet
    (<I>www.proxyvote.com</I>);</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">by scanning the QR code on your proxy card, notice of internet availability of proxy materials, or voting instruction form with your mobile device;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>

    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">via telephone by calling 1-800-690-6903;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>

    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">if you received a proxy card or voting instruction form in the mail, by completing, signing, dating, and returning your proxy card or voting instruction form in the return envelope provided to you in accordance with the instructions provided with the proxy card or voting instruction form; or</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>

    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">in person, at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. You must bring proof of ownership of Shares as of the record date in order to attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt"> <FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">See page 88 for a description of acceptable forms of proof of Share ownership.</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If you vote via the internet, by scanning
the QR code, or via telephone, you must vote no later than 11:59 p.m. Eastern time on June 5, 2014. If you return a proxy card
by mail, it must be received before the polls close at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. If your Shares are held through
a Walmart 401(k) plan, earlier voting deadlines apply. See page 86.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; padding-bottom: 1pt; padding-left: 2pt">Strategic Planning and Finance Committee</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: right">6</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: right">50</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: left">%</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt">&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: Black 2px solid; text-align: left">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="border-bottom: Black 2px solid; text-align: right">5</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 1pt; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>Director Independence and Tenure Balance</B></P>





<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; border: rgb(0,125,195) 2px solid">

    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding: 3pt; border-right: rgb(0,125,195) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">A majority of our Board nominees, and all current members of our
Audit Committee and CNGC, are independent. Despite their significant Share ownership, only three members of the Walton family are
members of our Board.</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding: 3pt"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Director nominees with a variety of tenures on our Board provide
an effective mix of deep knowledge of our company and fresh perspectives.</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC"><B>Recent Enhancements to Our Governance Practices
(page 31)</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; font-size: 9pt; padding-left: 2pt; border-top: Black 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: Black 2px solid; font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify; padding-right: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B><I>Special shareholders</I></B></FONT><B><I><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt">&rsquo;<SUB> </SUB><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">meetings</FONT></FONT></I></B><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"> can now be requested by shareholders holding 10% or more of Walmart&rsquo;s outstanding common stock.</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; background-color: White">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding-left: 2pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B><I>The role of the independent presiding director</I></B> has been expanded and clarified.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding-left: 2pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B><I>Stock ownership guidelines</I></B></FONT><B><I><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt">,</FONT></I></B><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt"> <FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">which were already robust, were strengthened for our senior executives. </FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; background-color: White">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding-left: 2pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Our senior executives&rsquo;
    compensation is now linked to achieving <B><I>compliance objectives</I></B></FONT><B><I><FONT STYLE="font-size: 9pt">.</FONT></I></B></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding-left: 2pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B><I>Enhanced recoupment provisions</I></B> have been added to our equity and cash incentive compensation plans.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC"><B>How We Pay for Performance (page 45)</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Our executive compensation program is intended to: provide fair,
competitive compensation based on performance and contributions to the company; provide incentives to attract and retain key executives;
instill a long-term commitment to the company; and encourage company ownership and align the interests of our key executives with
the interests of our shareholders, with the ultimate goal of driving long-term shareholder value. With these objectives in mind,
our executive compensation program includes the following key features:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 99%; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; padding-left: 3pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">on average, more than 50% of our NEOs&rsquo; target total direct compensation, or TDC, consists of long-term performance
    shares, and at least 70% of each NEO&rsquo;s fiscal 2014 target TDC is tied to financial performance;</TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-left: 3pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the financial metrics on which our NEOs&rsquo; pay is based &ndash; sales, return on investment, operating income, and/or
    gross merchandise value &ndash; are aligned with our key financial priorities of growth, leverage, and returns;</TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-left: 3pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">we seek to mitigate risk by using a combination of performance measures, linking a portion of each NEO&rsquo;s pay to
    the performance of the company as a whole, and capping maximum payouts tied to each performance measure;</TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-left: 3pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">we do not have any &ldquo;golden parachutes&rdquo; or other change-in-control provisions in our compensation plans or
    agreements with our Executive Officers; and</TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-left: 3pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">we provide only a limited number of perquisites to our Executive Officers.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC"><B>Primary Components of Our Fiscal 2014 Executive
Compensation Program (page 48)</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0"><A NAME="lwmta003"></A><FONT STYLE="font: 22pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC"><B>INFORMATION
ABOUT THE BOARD</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 30pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0.5in">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 99%; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 180pt"><A NAME="lwmta004"></A><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Proposal No.&nbsp;1</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B></B></FONT>Election of Directors</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,125,195) 2px solid"><B>What am I voting on?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">You are voting on a proposal to elect each of the nominees named
below as a director of the company. Your proxy holder will vote your Shares FOR the election of each of the Board&rsquo;s nominees
named below unless you instruct otherwise. If the shareholders elect all of the director nominees named in this proxy statement
at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, Walmart will have 14 directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,125,195) 2px solid"><B>What qualifications do the Compensation, Nominating and Governance
Committee and the Board consider when selecting candidates for nomination?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">In fulfilling its responsibility for identifying and evaluating
director candidates, in accordance with Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the CNGC selects potential candidates
on the basis of: outstanding achievement in their professional careers; broad experience and wisdom; personal and professional
integrity; ability to make independent, analytical inquiries; experience with and understanding of the business environment; willingness
and ability to devote adequate time to Board duties; and such other experience, attributes, and skills that the CNGC determines
qualify candidates for service on the Board.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Depending on the current composition of the Board and Board committees
and the company&rsquo;s current needs and business priorities, the CNGC generally seeks director candidates who possess experience,
skills, or background in one or more of the following areas:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif">
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; width: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; width: 30pt"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Senior leadership
experience. </B>We believe that directors who have served in relevant senior leadership positions bring unique experience and
perspective. We seek directors who have demonstrated expertise in governance, strategy, development, and execution.</FONT></TD>
    </TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: center; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x2.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="width: 22px; height: 35px"></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Technology and e-commerce experience. </B>E-commerce is a growing and important part of Walmart&rsquo;s global business. Directors with experience in e-commerce or related industries, such as the digital, mobile, and consumer internet industries, provide valuable insights and perspective to the Board.</FONT></TD>
    </TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x3.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Global or international business experience. </B>Because our company is a global organization, directors with broad international exposure provide useful business and cultural perspectives. We seek directors who have had relevant experience with multinational companies or in international markets.</FONT></TD>
    </TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x4.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Finance, accounting, or financial reporting experience. </B>Directors with an understanding of finance and financial reporting processes are valued on our company&rsquo;s Board because of the importance our company places on accurate financial reporting and robust financial controls and compliance. We also seek to have a number of directors who qualify as audit committee financial experts.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x5.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Retail experience. </B>As the world&rsquo;s largest retailer, we seek directors who possess an understanding of financial, operational, and strategic issues facing large retail companies. Directors with leadership experience in the global retail industry provide valuable insights to our Board.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x6.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Legal or regulatory experience. </B>Directors who have had legal or regulatory experience can provide insights into addressing significant legal and public policy issues, particularly in areas related to our company&rsquo;s business and operations. Because our company&rsquo;s business requires compliance with a variety of regulatory requirements across a number of countries, our Board values directors with relevant legal or regulatory experience.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; text-indent: 0in"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top"><IMG SRC="lwmt_x10x7.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Marketing, brand management, or public relations experience. </B>Directors who have had relevant experience in consumer marketing, brand management, and public relations, especially on a global basis, provide important insights to our Board.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify">The CNGC also considers whether a potential
candidate satisfies the independence and other requirements for service on the Board and its committees, as set forth in the NYSE
Listed Company Rules, the SEC&rsquo;s rules, and other applicable laws, rules, or regulations. Additional information regarding
qualifications for service on the Board and the nomination process for director candidates is set forth in the CNGC&rsquo;s charter
and our Corporate Governance Guidelines.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>10</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 10 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: justify"><B>Who are the 2014 director nominees?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The following candidates for election as directors at the 2014
Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting have been nominated by the Board based on the recommendation of the CNGC. The information set
forth below includes, with respect to each nominee, his or her age, principal occupation and employment during the past five years,
the year in which he or she first became a director of Walmart, each Board committee on which he or she currently serves, and directorships
of other public companies held by each nominee during the past five years.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC; text-align: left"><B>The Board recommends that shareholders vote
FOR each of the nominees named below for election to the Board.</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; color: #0066CC; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

    <TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">Ms. Craig is the recently retired CFO of Accenture plc (&ldquo;Accenture&rdquo;),
    a multinational management consulting, technology and outsourcing company, having served in that position from October 2006
    to June 2013. On July 1, 2013, Ms. Craig stepped down as CFO and retired from Accenture on August 31, 2013. She served in
    a variety of consulting, operational, and finance leadership roles at Accenture in her 34 years with the firm and its predecessor
    companies. Her three prior roles with Accenture from the time it became a public company were as senior vice president, finance,
    from March 2004 to October 2006, group director, business operations and services, from March 2003 to March 2004, and managing
    partner, global business operations, from June 2001 to March 2003.<BR>
    <BR>
    Ms. Craig serves as a member of the board of directors of Akamai Technologies, Inc., where she is currently the chair of the
    audit committee, and VMWare, Inc. She also serves on the board of directors and/or advisors of several private and charitable
    organizations.</TD>

other capacities, including responsibility for various international markets, since 1969. Mr. Daft served as a director of The
McGraw-Hill Companies, Inc. from 2003 to April 2012, Green Mountain Coffee Roasters, Inc. from December 2009 to May 2012, and
Sistema-Hals from September 2006 until December&nbsp;2009. Among additional endeavors, Mr. Daft is a member of the European Advisory
Council for N.M. Rothschild &amp; Sons Limited and a member of the advisory board of Longreach, Inc.</TD>

    served as Chairman from 2005 to 2010 and Chief Executive Officer from 2005 to 2008 of KPMG LLP in the U.S., the largest individual
    member firm of KPMG. Prior to serving as Chairman and CEO of KPMG LLP in the U.S., Mr. Flynn was Vice Chairman, Audit and
    Risk Advisory Services, with operating responsibility for the Audit, Risk Advisory, and Financial Advisory Services practices.
    Mr. Flynn serves as a member of the board of directors of The Chubb Corporation and JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. and as a member
    of the board of trustees of the University of St. Thomas, St. Paul, Minnesota. He has previously served as trustee of the
    Financial Accounting Standards Board, a member of the World Economic Forum&rsquo;s International Business Council, and was
    a founding member of The Prince of Wales&rsquo; International Integrated Reporting Committee.</TD>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; border: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 5pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: left; vertical-align: bottom; font-size: 14pt; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 5pt"><B>Marissa A. Mayer</B> </TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: right; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; padding-top: 5pt"><IMG SRC="lwmtx12x1.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx11x1.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx15x1.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx11x4.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 5pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><IMG SRC="lwmtx16x2.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="text-align: left; padding-top: 3pt"><B>Joined the Board: </B>2012 <BR> <B>Age: </B>38<BR> <B>Board Committees: </B>SPFC;
TeCC<BR> <B>Other Current Public Company Directorships: </B>Yahoo! Inc.<BR> <FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Independent Director</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 24%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 60%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 1%">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">Ms. Mayer is President and Chief Executive Officer and a member of the board of directors
of Yahoo! Inc. (&ldquo;Yahoo!&rdquo;), a digital media company, positions she has held since July 2012. Prior to assuming her
role at Yahoo!, Ms. Mayer was the Vice&nbsp;President of Local and Maps for Google Inc. (&ldquo;Google&rdquo;) beginning in 2010,
where she led the product management and engineering efforts of Google&rsquo;s local, mobile, and location-based products, including
Google Maps, Google Maps for Mobile, Local Search, Google Earth, and Street View. Ms. Mayer served in a variety of other capacities
after joining Google as its first female engineer in 1999, and was responsible for launching hundreds of products and features
during that time. Concurrently with her work at Google, Ms. Mayer taught introductory computer programming classes at Stanford
University. Ms. Mayer holds a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in symbolic systems and a master&rsquo;s degree in computer science from
Stanford University. Ms.&nbsp;Mayer serves on the board of directors of AliphCom (which does business as Jawbone) and on the boards
of the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art and the San Francisco Ballet.</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B><I>Skills and Qualifications:</I></B></FONT></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

<TD STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx12x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="text-align: justify">Ms. Mayer&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include her extensive expertise
and insight into the technology and consumer internet industries.</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

and strategic planning.</TD>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; border: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="padding-top: 5pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: left; vertical-align: bottom; font-size: 14pt; padding-top: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Steven S Reinemund</B></FONT></TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; padding-top: 5pt"><IMG SRC="lwmtx11x1.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx11x4.jpg" ALT="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx15x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 5pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><IMG SRC="lwmtx18x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><B>Joined the Board: </B>2010<BR> <B>Age: </B>66 <BR>
<B>Board Committee: </B>SPFC (Chair)<BR> <B>Other Current Public Company Directorships: </B>Exxon Mobil Corporation; American Express Company;<BR> Marriott International, Inc. &nbsp; <BR>
<FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>Independent Director</B></Font></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 24%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify; width: 60%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 1%">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">Mr. Reinemund is the Dean of Business and Professor of Leadership and Strategy at Wake Forest University, positions he has held since July 2008. Prior to joining the faculty of Wake Forest University, Mr. Reinemund had a distinguished 23-year career with PepsiCo, Inc. (&ldquo;PepsiCo&rdquo;), where he served as that company&rsquo;s Chairman of the Board from October 2006 to May 2007, and Chairman and CEO from May 2001 to October 2006. Prior to becoming Chairman and CEO, Mr. Reinemund was PepsiCo&rsquo;s President and Chief Operating Officer from 1999 to 2001 and Chairman and CEO of Frito-Lay&rsquo;s worldwide operations from 1996 to 1999. Mr. Reinemund has served as a director of Exxon Mobil Corporation, American Express Company, and Marriott International, Inc., all since 2007. He previously served as a director of Johnson &amp; Johnson from 2003 to 2008. Mr. Reinemund is also a member of the board of trustees for The Cooper Institute.</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B><I>Skills and Qualifications:</I></B></FONT></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="4" STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;<IMG SRC="lwmtx11x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="text-align: justify">Mr. Reinemund has international business leadership experience gained through his service as Chairman and CEO of a major global public company. In addition, through his service as dean of a prominent business school and on the boards of several large companies in a variety of industries, including his service on the Board and his prior service on the CNGC, Mr. Reinemund is able to provide considerable corporate governance, finance, operational, and strategic expertise to the Board.</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: justify"><B>Are there any directors not standing for reelection?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Yes. In accordance with our company&rsquo;s historical practice
regarding our company&rsquo;s previous CEOs&rsquo; service on the Board and our Corporate Governance Guidelines, H. Lee Scott,
Jr. and Christopher J. Williams, each of whom currently serves on the Board, will rotate off the Board at the conclusion of their
current term and will not stand for reelection at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

    Lee Scott, Jr.</B></FONT></TD>

    <!-- Field: /Page -->

    <P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>What is the nomination process for director candidates?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The CNGC has primary responsibility for identifying,
evaluating, and recommending potential director candidates to the Board. The CNGC&rsquo;s process for board succession planning
and&nbsp;identifying potential candidates for nomination to the Board is an ongoing one. Throughout the year, the CNGC actively
engages in director succession planning and regularly evaluates whether the addition of a director or directors with particular
attributes, experience, or skills would contribute to enhancing the Board&rsquo;s effectiveness, achieving the company&rsquo;s
business objectives, and serving our company&rsquo;s and shareholders&rsquo; long-term best interests.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">As a part of the process of identifying potential
director candidates, the CNGC may consult with other directors and senior officers and may engage a search firm to assist in the
process. Spencer Stuart currently serves as our company&rsquo;s director candidate search consultant. In this capacity, Spencer
Stuart seeks out candidates who have the desired skills, experience, and other attributes that the CNGC has identified for potential
candidates, conducts an extensive search for, and analysis of, potential candidates, and then presents the most qualified candidates
to the CNGC and our Chairman. If the CNGC decides, on the basis of its preliminary review, to proceed with further consideration
of a potential candidate, the Chair of the CNGC and other members of the CNGC, as well as other members of the Board, as appropriate,
may interview the candidate. The CNGC then either makes its recommendation to the Board to fill a vacancy or add an additional
member or recommends to the Board a slate of candidates for nomination for election to the Board. Pamela J. Craig, who was appointed
by the Board as a director on November 22, 2013 to fill a newly created vacancy on the Board, was initially identified as a potential
candidate for the Board by Spencer Stuart and her appointment was a result of the process outlined above. C. Douglas McMillon was
appointed as a director by the Board in connection with the Board appointing him as Walmart&rsquo;s President and CEO, and not
as a result of the candidate search process described above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">S. Robson Walton and Jim C. Walton are members
of a group that beneficially owns more than five percent of the outstanding Shares. Any participation by either of them in the
nomination process is considered to be in their capacities as members of the Board and is not considered to be a recommendation
from security holders who beneficially own more than five percent of the outstanding Shares.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>Does the Board consider diversity in the nomination process?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Yes. As provided in our company&rsquo;s Corporate
Governance Guidelines, the Board is committed to diversified membership. The Board will not discriminate on the basis of race,
color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, religion, or disability in selecting nominees. Diversity and inclusion are
values embedded into Walmart&rsquo;s culture and fundamental to its business. In keeping with those values, when assessing a candidate,
the CNGC and the Board consider the different viewpoints and experiences that a candidate could bring to the Board and how those
viewpoints and experiences could enhance the Board&rsquo;s effectiveness in the execution of its responsibilities. In addition,
the Board assesses the diversity of the Board and Board committees as a part of its annual self-evaluation process.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>Can shareholders recommend director candidates?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">Yes. Shareholders may recommend candidates for consideration by the
Board by writing to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. Board of Directors<BR>
c/o Gordon Y. Allison, Vice President and General Counsel,<BR>
Corporate Division<BR>
702 Southwest 8<SUP>th </SUP>Street<BR>
Bentonville, Arkansas 72716-0215</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">The recommendation must include the following information:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the candidate&rsquo;s name and business address;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a resume or curriculum vitae that demonstrates the candidate&rsquo;s qualifications to serve as a director as described on page 10 and in our Corporate Governance Guidelines;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a statement as to whether or not, during the past ten years, the candidate has been convicted in a criminal proceeding (other than for minor traffic violations), has been involved in any other legal proceeding or has been the subject of, or a party to, any order, judgment, decree, finding or sanction (including any order, judgment, decree, finding or sanction issued by an entity such as a stock or commodities exchange) relating to an alleged violation of laws or regulations relating to securities, commodities, financial institutions, insurance companies, mail or wire fraud, or fraud in connection with a business entity, in each case giving the date and a brief description of the conviction, order, judgment, decree, finding, or sanction, the name of the proceeding, and the disposition;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>21</B></P>


<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 21 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a statement from the candidate that he or she consents to act as a director of our company if elected; and</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a statement from the person submitting the candidate that he or she is a record holder of Shares, or, if that person is not a record holder of Shares, a written statement from the record holder of Shares (usually a broker, bank, or other nominee) beneficially owned by that person verifying that, at the time that person submitted the candidate, he or she was a beneficial owner of Shares.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">All candidates recommended for nomination to
the Board by a shareholder pursuant to the requirements above will be submitted to the CNGC for its review and will be evaluated
by the CNGC on the same basis as all other director candidates.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">See &ldquo;Submission of Shareholder Proposals&rdquo;
on page 89 for information regarding how shareholders may bring business before Walmart&rsquo;s annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings,
either through the shareholder proposal process or pursuant to the advance notice provisions of Walmart&rsquo;s Bylaws.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>How often are directors elected?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">All of Walmart&rsquo;s director nominees are
submitted to shareholders for election at each annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting and hold office until the next annual shareholders&rsquo;
meeting and until their successors are duly elected and qualified or until their earlier resignation, death, or removal. Each of
the 14 director nominees named in this proxy statement currently serves on the Board and was elected by the shareholders at the
2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, with the exception of Pamela J.&nbsp;Craig and C. Douglas McMillon, both of whom were
appointed as directors by the Board on November 22, 2013.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Each incumbent director is a nominee for election
as a director at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, with the exception of H. Lee Scott, Jr., and Christopher J. Williams,
who will not be standing for reelection. The Board has authority under the Bylaws to fill vacancies and to increase or, upon the
occurrence of a vacancy, decrease the Board&rsquo;s size between annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings. The Board has established
the size of the Board immediately after the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting to be 14 directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>What if a nominee is unwilling or unable to serve as a director?</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Each director nominee named in this proxy statement
has previously consented to act as a director of Walmart if elected. If a nominee becomes unwilling or unable to serve as a director,
your proxy holder will have the authority to vote your Shares for any substitute candidate nominated by the Board, or the Board
may decrease the size of the Board.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: #0066CC"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta005"></A><B>Director Independence</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">A majority of our directors must be independent
in accordance with the independence requirements set forth in the NYSE Listed Company Rules. In addition, the Audit Committee and
the CNGC must be composed solely of directors who meet additional, heightened independence standards applicable to members of audit
committees and compensation committees under the NYSE Listed Company Rules and the SEC&rsquo;s rules.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">In making independence determinations, the Board
complies with all NYSE and SEC criteria and considers all relevant facts and circumstances. Under the NYSE Listed Company Rules,
to be considered independent:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the director must not have a disqualifying relationship, as defined in the NYSE Listed Company Rules; and</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Board must affirmatively determine that the director otherwise has no direct or indirect material relationship with our company. To aid in the director independence assessment process, the Board has adopted materiality guidelines that identify the following categories of relationships that the Board has determined will generally not affect a director&rsquo;s independence.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>22</B></P>
