    <!-- Field: /Page -->



<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%">
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 24%; vertical-align: bottom; padding-left: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Materiality Guideline</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify; width: 1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: left; width: 75%; padding-right: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Description</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 3pt; border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Ordinary Retail Transactions</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify; border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt; border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director, an entity with which a director is affiliated, or one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family, purchased property or services from Walmart in retail transactions on terms generally available to Walmart Associates during Walmart&rsquo;s last fiscal year.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Immaterial Ownership</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director or one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family owns or has owned during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year, directly or indirectly, 5% or less of an entity that has a business relationship with Walmart.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Immaterial Transactions</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director or one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family owns or has owned during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year, directly or indirectly, more than 5% of an entity that has a business relationship with Walmart so long as the amount paid to or received from Walmart during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year accounts for less than $1,000,000 or, if greater, 1% of the entity&rsquo;s consolidated gross revenues for that entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year.</FONT><BR>
<BR>
<FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director or a member of the director&rsquo;s immediate family is or has been during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year an executive officer or employee of an entity that made payments to, or received payments from, Walmart during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year that account for less than $1,000,000 or, if greater, 1% of the entity&rsquo;s consolidated gross revenues for that entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Immaterial Positions</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director or one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family is a director or trustee or was a director or trustee (but not an executive officer or employee) of an entity during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year that has a business or charitable relationship with Walmart and that made payments to, or received payments from, Walmart during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year in an amount representing less than $5,000,000 or, if greater, 5% of the entity&rsquo;s consolidated gross revenues for that entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year.</FONT><BR>
<BR>
<FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Walmart paid to, employed, or retained one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family for compensation not exceeding $120,000 during Walmart&rsquo;s last fiscal year.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 3pt; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Immaterial Benefits</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: center; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The director or one or more members of the director&rsquo;s immediate family received from Walmart, during Walmart&rsquo;s last fiscal year, personal benefits having an aggregate value of less than $5,000.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">In April 2014, the Board and the CNGC conducted
their annual review of directors&rsquo; responses to a questionnaire soliciting information regarding their direct and indirect
relationships with the company (and the directors&rsquo; immediate family members&rsquo; direct and indirect relationships with
the company) and other relationships that may be relevant to independence, as well as due diligence performed by management regarding
any transactions, relationships, or arrangements between the company and the directors or parties related to the directors. As
a result of this&nbsp;review, the Board has determined that the following director nominees are Independent Directors under the
independence standards set forth in the NYSE Listed Company Rules: Aida M. Alvarez; James I. Cash, Jr.; Roger C. Corbett; Pamela&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Craig;
Douglas N. Daft; Timothy P. Flynn; Marissa A. Mayer; Steven S Reinemund; and Linda S. Wolf. The Board has also determined that
Christopher J. Williams, who is not standing for reelection at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, is an Independent Director.
In addition, the Board determined that the currently serving members of the Audit Committee and the CNGC meet the heightened independence
standards for membership on those Board committees. The Board also determined that James W. Breyer, M. Michele Burns, and Arne
M. Sorenson, who did not stand for reelection at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting and, therefore, ceased to be directors
of Walmart on June 7, 2013, were independent during the portion of fiscal 2014 during which they served on the Board.</P>
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>23</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 23 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">In making its determination as to the independence
of our Independent Directors, the Board considered whether any relationship between a director and Walmart is a material relationship
based on the materiality guidelines discussed above, the facts and circumstances of the relationship, the amounts involved in the
relationship, the director&rsquo;s interest in such relationship, if any, and such other factors as the Board, in its judgment,
deemed appropriate. In each case, the Board found the relationship with our Independent Directors to be immaterial to the director&rsquo;s
independence. The types of relationships considered by the Board are noted below:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Walmart director was an officer of a Walmart vendor: Ms. Mayer; </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">immediate family members of the Walmart director were employees or officers of Walmart vendors or service providers: Ms. Alvarez, Ms. Craig, Mr. Corbett, Mr. Reinemund, and Ms. Wolf;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Walmart director was also a director or trustee of a Walmart vendor or service provider: Dr. Cash, Ms. Craig, Mr. Flynn, Ms. Mayer, Mr. Reinemund, Mr. Williams, and Ms. Wolf; and</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 5pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Walmart director was a member of the board of trustees or advisory board of, or held a position in, a not-for-profit institution, entity, association, or organization to which Walmart made or committed to make donations in amounts that were, in each case, less than $120,000: Ms. Alvarez and Mr. Reinemund.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">All of the relationships and transactions of
the types described in the preceding paragraph fit within our materiality guidelines, with the exception of certain relationships
involving immediate family members of Ms. Craig, Mr. Corbett, and Mr. Reinemund. In each of these instances, an immediate family
member of one of our directors is employed by (but is not an executive officer of) a Walmart supplier or vendor that received payments
from Walmart during the entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year that account for more than 1% of the entity&rsquo;s consolidated gross
revenues for that entity&rsquo;s last fiscal year. The Board determined these relationships were immaterial to each director&rsquo;s
independence because in each case the immediate family member: (i) is not an executive officer of the entity; (ii) is not involved
in the negotiation of transactions or the business relationship between Walmart and the entity; (iii) does not receive compensation
from the entity based on the marketing or sale of the entity&rsquo;s goods or services to Walmart; and (iv) did not have his or
her advancement within such entity based on the marketing or sale of the entity&rsquo;s goods or services to Walmart. Further,
the payments made by Walmart to the entities, or by the entities to Walmart, were for various products and services in the ordinary
course of business, and Walmart has had a relationship with these entities for many years prior to the directors&rsquo; immediate
family members&rsquo; employment with these entities.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Board and the CNGC concluded that the Independent
Directors do not currently have and have not had during the last three years relationships (including all transactions disclosed
under &ldquo;Related Person Transactions&rdquo; on page 40) that: (i) constitute disqualifying relationships under the NYSE Listed
Company Rules; (ii) otherwise compromise the independence of the named directors; or (iii) otherwise constitute a material relationship
between Walmart and the directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta006"></A><B>Board Meetings</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Board held a total of six meetings during fiscal 2014 to review
significant developments affecting our company, engage in strategic planning, and act on matters requiring Board approval. During
fiscal 2014, each incumbent director attended at least 85 percent of the aggregate number of Board meetings and meetings of Board
committees on which he or she served. As a whole, during fiscal 2014, our incumbent directors attended approximately 97 percent
of the aggregate number of Board meetings and meetings of Board committees on which they served. The Outside Directors and Independent
Directors met regularly in executive sessions, with the presiding director chairing those sessions.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta007"></A><B>Director Onboarding and Engagement with the Business</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">All of our Board members are expected to gain
an in-depth understanding of our business and operations in order to enhance their strategic value to our Board. Shortly after
joining our Board, each new director is partnered in a mutual mentoring relationship with a member of senior management, and each
new director has &ldquo;learn the business&rdquo; meetings with the leaders of key operational and corporate support functions.
At least once per year, a Board meeting is held at a location away from our home office, usually in an international market in
which we operate. In connection with these Board meetings, our directors learn more about that market and our business in that
market through meetings with our business leaders in the markets, visits to our stores and other facilities in the local market,
and visits to the stores of our competitors. Our Board members also engage directly with our Associates at a variety of events
throughout the year. Activities and events that members of our Board participated in since the beginning of fiscal 2014 include:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; padding-bottom: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-bottom: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Traveling with members of our senior management to visit international markets, including Chile, Brazil, and Africa;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Speaking at the inaugural summit of our Global Governance organization;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta008"></A><B>Board Committees</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Board has six standing committees: the Audit Committee; the Compensation,
Nominating and Governance Committee; the Executive Committee; the Global Compensation Committee; the Strategic Planning and Finance
Committee; and the Technology and eCommerce Committee. As described above, the Board has determined that all of the members of
the Audit Committee and the Compensation, Nominating and Governance Committee are independent directors as defined in the SEC&rsquo;s
rules and regulations and the NYSE Listed Company Rules. The charters for each committee may be found on Walmart&rsquo;s website
at <I>www.stock.walmart.com</I> in the &ldquo;Corporate Governance&rdquo; section.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">The charts below summarize the membership of each committee, as well
as the roles and responsibilities of each committee.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">I = Determined by the Board to be independent under the NYSE and applicable
SEC rules and regulations</P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0"><IMG SRC="lwtmx25x3.jpg" ALT=""> = Chairman of the Board</P>

rules and regulations</P>

<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 0 0 5pt">F = Determined by the Board to be an Audit Committee Financial Expert
as defined under applicable SEC rules and regulations</P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 0 0 5pt">I = Determined by the Board to be independent under the NYSE Listed
Company Rules and applicable SEC rules and regulations</P>

    <TD STYLE="font-size: 1px; width: 2pt; text-align: right">&nbsp;</TD>

    <P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 0 0 9pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -9pt"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews matters relating to information technology, eCommerce, and innovation and oversees the integration of Walmart&rsquo;s information technology, eCommerce, and innovation efforts with Walmart&rsquo;s overall strategy</P>
    <P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 0 0 9pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -9pt"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and provides guidance regarding trends in technology and eCommerce and monitors overall industry trends</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 9pt; width: 23%; padding-left: 3pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Gregory B. Penner (C)</FONT><BR>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">C = Committee Chair</P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">I = Determined by the Board to be independent under the NYSE Listed
Company Rules</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta009"></A><B>Compensation of the Directors</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">As described below, the base compensation for
Outside Directors consists of a Share award and an annual retainer. During fiscal 2014, Michael T. Duke, C. Douglas McMillon, and
S. Robson Walton received compensation only for their services as Associates of our company and not in their capacities as directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">For service on the Board for the term beginning
upon election at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting on June 7, 2013, each Outside Director received an annual Share award
on June&nbsp;7, 2013. The number of Shares awarded was determined by dividing $175,000 by the closing price of the Shares on the
NYSE on the date of the grant, rounded to the nearest Share. This annual Share award was paid directly in Shares or deferred in
stock units, as elected by each Outside Director. In addition, each Outside Director is entitled to receive an annual retainer,
payable in arrears in equal quarterly installments. For the Board term that commenced upon election at the 2012 Annual Shareholders&rsquo;
Meeting, this annual retainer was $60,000. Upon election at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, which occurred on June
7, 2013, this annual retainer increased to $75,000. This annual retainer can be received in the form of cash, in Shares (determined
by dividing the dollar amount of the quarterly installment by the closing price of the Shares on the NYSE on the payment date of
the quarterly installment) rounded to the nearest whole Share, deferred in stock units, or deferred into an interest-credited cash
account, as elected by each Outside Director.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Outside Directors who serve as the chair
of a Board committee receive an additional retainer for the additional time required for Board committee business. During fiscal
2014, the retainer for the chairs of the Audit Committee and CNGC was $25,000, and the retainer for the chairs of the SPFC and
TeCC was $20,000. In addition, Outside Directors who serve on more than one standing Board committee receive an additional $15,000
annually. Further, the director appointed by the Board to serve as the presiding director of executive sessions of the Outside
Directors and Independent Directors receives an additional $20,000 annually. These additional fees are payable in arrears in equal
quarterly installments, and as noted above, may be taken in cash, in Shares (determined by dividing the dollar value of the amount
of the additional fees by the closing price of the Shares on the NYSE on the payment date of the quarterly installment to such
directors) rounded to the nearest whole Share, deferred in stock units, or deferred into an interest-credited cash account, as
elected by each Outside Director. Finally, each Outside Director who attends in person a Board meeting held at a location that
requires intercontinental travel from his or her residence is paid a $4,000 meeting attendance fee. This additional fee is intended
to compensate our Outside Directors for the additional time required to travel intercontinentally, and may be taken in any of the
forms available for the annual retainer, as elected by each Outside Director.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Since November 2011, the Audit Committee has
been conducting an internal investigation into, among other things, alleged violations of the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act
of 1977 (the &ldquo;FCPA&rdquo;) and other alleged crimes or misconduct in connection with foreign subsidiaries, and whether prior
allegations of such violations and/or misconduct were appropriately handled by Walmart. The Audit Committee and Walmart have engaged
outside counsel from a number of law firms and other advisors who are assisting in the ongoing investigation of these matters.
This investigation has resulted in a significant increase in the workload of the Audit Committee members since the commencement
of this investigation, and during fiscal 2014, the Audit Committee conducted 13 additional meetings related to the investigation
and compliance matters, and Audit Committee members received frequent updates via conference calls and other means of communication
with outside counsel and other advisors related to the investigation. As it had done in November 2012 in recognition of the significantly
increased commitment of time required of the Audit Committee to conduct this investigation, in November 2013, the CNGC and the
Board approved an additional annual fee in the amount of $75,000 payable to each Audit Committee member other than the Audit Committee
Chair for fiscal 2014, and an additional annual fee in the amount of $100,000 payable to the Audit Committee Chair for fiscal 2014.
These amounts were prorated for directors who served on the Audit Committee during a portion of fiscal 2014. The CNGC determined
the amounts of these additional fees based on (1) the CNGC&rsquo;s and the Board&rsquo;s review of the significant additional time
and effort that had been required of the Audit Committee members during the previous Board term in connection with these matters,
which were in addition to the time spent by the Audit Committee with respect to the Audit Committee&rsquo;s other duties and its
regularly scheduled meetings, and (2) the expectation that the Audit Committee members would continue to expend approximately the
same amount of time and effort in discharging their responsibilities as Audit Committee members at least through the remainder
of fiscal 2014.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Board has adopted stock ownership guidelines
for the Outside Directors. Each Outside Director must own, within five years of his or her initial election or appointment to the
Board, an amount of Shares or stock units having a value equal to five times the annual retainer component of the Outside Director&rsquo;s
compensation approved by the Board in the year the director was initially elected or appointed. All Outside Directors who have
reached the five-year compliance date own Shares having a value exceeding this requirement.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Pursuant to the CNGC&rsquo;s charter, director
compensation for the Outside Directors is reviewed at least annually by the CNGC, which recommends to the Board the annual compensation
for those directors. The compensation paid to the directors during fiscal 2014 is described in the table below.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>28</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 28 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>

<P STYLE="font: 3pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 15pt; font-size: 8pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">(1)</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; font-size: 8pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The table omits the columns for &ldquo;Option Awards&rdquo; and &ldquo;Non-Equity Incentive Plan Compensation&rdquo; because our company neither issues stock options to, nor provides non-equity incentive compensation for, Outside Directors. Michael T. Duke, C. Douglas McMillon, and S. Robson Walton are omitted from this table because they received compensation only as Associates of our company during fiscal 2014 and did not receive any additional compensation for their duties as directors. The compensation for Mr. Duke and Mr. McMillon for fiscal 2014 is disclosed in the Summary Compensation table on page 64. Mr. Walton&rsquo;s annual salary as Chairman of Walmart is equal to the amount of the annual stock and cash retainer paid to Outside Directors, and is therefore currently $250,000. During fiscal 2014, our company also paid health insurance premiums for Mr. Duke, Mr. McMillon, and Mr. Walton on the same basis as for other Associates, and made 401(k) Plan matching contributions to Mr. Duke and Mr. McMillon on the same basis as for other Associates. Mr. Duke, Mr. McMillon, and Mr. Walton are also eligible to participate in our company&rsquo;s other benefit plans, such as our medical insurance plan and Stock Purchase Plan, on the same basis as all other Associates.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="font-size: 8pt; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">(2)</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; font-size: 8pt; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">This column represents the annual retainer paid to directors, the Board committee chair retainers, the additional payment to certain Outside Directors for serving on multiple Board committees, the additional payment to the presiding director, the additional payments to certain directors for attendance at Board meetings that required intercontinental travel from his or her residence, and the additional fee paid to members of the Audit Committee described above. The following directors elected to receive the amounts included in this column in the form of Shares, rounded to the nearest whole Share, in lieu of cash:</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: bottom; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">In
    accordance with SEC rules, the amounts included in this column are the aggregate grant date fair value for stock awards granted
    in fiscal 2014, computed in accordance with the stock-based accounting rules that are a part of GAAP (as set forth in Financial
    Accounting Standards Board&rsquo;s Accounting Standards Codification Topic 718). Each Outside Director elected to the Board
    at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting received a stock award of 2,293 Shares on June 7, 2013. The number of Shares
    was determined by dividing $175,000 by $76.33, which was the closing price of a Share on the NYSE on the grant date, rounded
    to the nearest whole Share. Upon her appointment to the Board on November 22, 2013, Ms. Craig received a stock award of 1,177
    Shares. The number of Shares was determined by dividing $93,973 (a prorated portion of the $175,000 annual stock award value)
    by $79.81, which was the closing price of a Share on the NYSE on the grant date, and rounding to the nearest whole Share.
    Dr. Cash, Mr. Daft, Mr. Flynn, Ms. Mayer, Mr. Penner, Mr. Scott, Mr. Walton, and Ms. Wolf deferred the receipt of these Shares
    until a later date. No current Outside Directors held options to purchase Shares as of the end of fiscal 2014. Options held
    by Mr. Duke and Mr. McMillon at the end of fiscal 2014 are disclosed in the Outstanding Equity Awards at Fiscal 2014 Year-End
    table below. The options held by Mr. Duke and Mr. McMillon were granted to them in prior years as part of their compensation
    for service as Associates of Walmart and not as compensation for serving as a director of our company.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: bottom">

    amounts in this column represent above-market interest earned on director compensation deferred to an interest-credited account
    under the Director Compensation Deferral Plan, as elected by the director. The interest rate on the interest-bearing account
    is set pursuant to the terms of the Director Compensation Deferral Plan based on the ten-year United States Treasury note
    yield on the first day of January plus 2.70 percent. This rate was 4.56 percent for the calendar year ended December 31, 2013,
    and increased to 5.70 percent for the calendar year ending December 31, 2014.</FONT></TD></TR>

    <P STYLE="font: 22pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><A NAME="lwmta010"></A><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE</B></FONT>.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><A NAME="lwmta011"></A><B>Walmart Governance Highlights</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 3pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<DIV STYLE="padding: 3pt; width: 99%; border: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid">




<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 9pt; color: White">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; color: White">
    <TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 2pt 1pt; background-color: rgb(51,153,204); color: White; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,104) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 3pt; border-bottom: White 1px solid; color: White"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;RECENT
                                                                                                                                                                                                   GOVERNANCE
                                                                                                                                                                                                   ENHANCEMENTS</B></P>

</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; color: White">
    <TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 5pt; background-color: rgb(51,153,204); color: White; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0; margin-bottom: 0pt; color: White">Recent enhancements further reinforce our commitment to exemplary corporate governance practices.</P>

</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt; color: White">
    <TD STYLE="width: 49%; font-size: 9pt; padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 5pt; background-color: rgb(51,153,204); color: White; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; color: White">&bull;&#9;<B><I>Special
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Shareholders&rsquo;
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Meetings.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   </I></B>Shareholders
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   holding
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   10%
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   or
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   more
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   of
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Walmart&rsquo;s
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   outstanding
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Shares
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   may
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   now
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   request
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   special
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   shareholders&rsquo;
                                                                                                                                                                                                                   meetings.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; color: White">&bull;&#9;<B><I>Expanded
Role of Presiding Director.</I></B> The Board recently enhanced the role of the Board&rsquo;s independent presiding director.
See page 33 for additional information.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; color: White">&bull;&#9;<B><I>Linking
Executive Incentive Compensation to Compliance.</I></B> For fiscal 2014, the annual cash incentive payments to each of our NEOs
and certain other Executive Officers were subject to achieving certain compliance objectives. See page 54 for additional information.</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 2%; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; background-color: rgb(51,153,204); color: White; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 49%; font-size: 9pt; padding-right: 5pt; background-color: rgb(51,153,204); color: White; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-left: 5pt"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; color: White">&bull;<B>&#9;<I>Increased
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Stock
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Ownership
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Guidelines.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    </I></B>In
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    fiscal
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    2014,
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    the&nbsp;Board
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    strengthened
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    the
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    stock
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    ownership
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    guidelines
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    for
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    our
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    senior
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    executives.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    See
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    page
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    62
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    for
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    additional
                                                                                                                                                                                                                    information.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; color: White">&bull;<B>&#9;<I>Enhanced
Compensation Recoupment Provisions Under Incentive Plans.</I></B> In fiscal 2014, the Board amended the MIP and the Stock Incentive
Plan to enhance the CNGC&rsquo;s authority to require participants to reimburse the company for equity awards or cash incentive
payments made to such participants if the CNGC determines such participants engaged in acts detrimental to the best interests
of the company. See page 62 for additional information.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 9pt">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt">
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; padding-left: 5pt; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt"><P STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; margin-right: 5pt"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;KEY
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                GOVERNANCE
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                POLICIES</B></P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; padding-left: 7pt; background-color: White; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); padding-left: 5pt; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt"><P STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; margin-right: 5pt">&nbsp;<B>&nbsp;COMPENSATION
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                GOVERNANCE</B></p></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt">
    <TD STYLE="width: 25%; font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 5pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Annual election
        of directors who serve one-year terms (page 22)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Majority vote standard
        in uncontested director elections; incumbent directors who do not receive a majority vote must offer their resignations
        (page 84)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Separation of Chairman
        and CEO roles for more than 25 years (page&nbsp;33)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Board and Board
        committees conduct annual self-evaluations to identify areas in which effectiveness can be enhanced (page 35)</P>
        <P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 24%; font-size: 9pt; padding-right: 5pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 5pt"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Directors have full
        and free access to officers, other Associates, and the company&rsquo;s outside advisors</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;CNGC provides independent
        oversight of the company&rsquo;s legislative affairs and public policy engagement strategy (page 35)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;CNGC and Board regularly
engage in rigorous director and Executive Officer succession planning (page 35)&nbsp;</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 2%; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; background-color: White; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 5pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 25%; font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 5pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Executive compensation
        programs closely linked to performance (page 45)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;A significant majority
        of our NEOs&rsquo; compensation is performance-based and exposed to fluctuations in the price of our common stock (page
        50)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Annual shareholder
        advisory vote on the compensation of our NEOs&nbsp;(page 74)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Robust stock ownership
        guidelines for our directors, NEOs, and other senior officers (page 62)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Insider Trading Policy prohibits
directors and Executive Officers from using Shares as collateral</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 24%; font-size: 9pt; padding-right: 5pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 5pt"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt">for margin loans and from
        engaging in hedging and similar transactions&nbsp;(page&nbsp;63)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Directors and Executive
        Officers are prohibited from pledging Shares for non-margin loans without the pre-approval of Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate
        Secretary; any pledged Shares are not considered in determining compliance with our stock ownership guidelines&nbsp;(page 63)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Since 2007, the CNGC has
engaged an independent consultant on executive compensation matters (page&nbsp;58)&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 9pt">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt">

    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; padding-left: 5pt; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-top: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt"><P STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; margin-right: 5pt"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;INDEPENDENCE</B></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font-size: 9pt">
    <TD STYLE="width: 25%; font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 10pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;No &ldquo;poison
        pill&rdquo; or similar shareholder rights plan</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Shareholders holding
        10% or more of the company&rsquo;s common stock may request special shareholders&rsquo; meetings</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Walmart conducts extensive
shareholder outreach throughout the year (page 36)</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 24%; font-size: 9pt; padding-right: 5pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 10pt"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;No supermajority
        voting requirements</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Appointment of the
        company&rsquo;s independent accountants is submitted annually to shareholders for ratification (page 41)</P>
        <P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 2%; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; background-color: White; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 25%; font-size: 9pt; padding: 2pt 5pt 10pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-left: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Nine of 14 director
        nominees are independent (page 23)</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 2pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Audit Committee
        and CNGC comprised solely of Independent Directors&nbsp;(page 23)</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt">&bull;&#9;Independent presiding
director with enhanced role and responsibilities (page 33)</P></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 24%; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; padding: 2pt 5pt 10pt 7pt; text-indent: -7pt; background-color: rgb(216,228,228); border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid; border-right: rgb(0,102,204) 1px solid"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;&#9;Board
    and Board committees have the power to hire independent advisors, as they deem appropriate, without management consultation</FONT></TD></TR>

</div>

    <P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta012"></A>Board and Committee Governing
Documents</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; ">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Each standing committee of the Board has
a written charter, which sets forth the roles and responsibilities of the Board committee. In addition, the Board has adopted Corporate
Governance Guidelines, as more specifically described below. Those charters, along with the company&rsquo;s Corporate Governance
Guidelines, provide the overall framework for our corporate governance practices. Our Corporate Governance Guidelines address,
among other topics:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">director qualifications and nomination requirements; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</font></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Board size, structure, and composition; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</font></td>

and Senior Financial Officers supplements Walmart&rsquo;s Statement of Ethics, which is applicable to all directors, Executive
Officers, and Associates and is also available at <I>www.walmartethics.com.</I> A description of any substantive amendment or
waiver of Walmart&rsquo;s Code of Ethics for the CEO and Senior Financial Officers or Walmart&rsquo;s Statement of Ethics granted
to Executive Officers or directors will be disclosed on our corporate website (<I>http://stock.walmart. com/corporate-governance/governance-documents</I>)
for a period of 12 months after the date of the amendment or waiver. There were no substantive amendments or waivers of Walmart&rsquo;s
Code of Ethics for the CEO and Senior Financial Officers or Walmart&rsquo;s Statement of Ethics granted to Executive Officers
or directors during fiscal 2014.</P>
