<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta013"></A>Board Leadership Structure</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>
<DIV STYLE="padding: 5pt; border: Black 1px solid; width: 99%; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Chairman:<I> S. Robson Walton </I></B><I>&ndash;
    </I>presides over meetings of the Board and shareholders; provides advice and counsel to the CEO and other officers; focuses
    on oversight and governance matters </FONT></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Presiding Director:<I> James I. Cash,
    Jr.</I></B><I> &ndash;</I> Independent Director; presides over the executive sessions of the Outside Directors and Independent
    Directors and performs the additional duties described below under the heading &ldquo;Presiding Director&rdquo; </FONT></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>CEO:<I> C. Douglas McMillon </I></B><I>&ndash;
    </I>responsible for the general management and supervision of the business of our company and effectuating directives of the
    Board </FONT></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Additional information about Mr. Walton, Dr. Cash, and Mr. McMillon may be found on pages 19, 12, and 17, respectively.</font></td></tr>
</table>
</div>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Separation of Chairman and CEO Roles.
</I></B>In accordance with our Corporate Governance Guidelines, we have separated the roles of the Chairman and the CEO of our
company since 1988. We separate these roles in recognition of the differences between the two roles and the value to our company
of having the distinct and different perspectives and experiences of a separate Chairman and CEO. Our CEO is responsible for the
day-to-day management and supervision of the business and affairs of our company (such as reviewing performance and allocating
resources as the company&rsquo;s chief operating decision maker) and for ensuring that the directives of the Board are carried
into effect. Our Chairman, on the other hand, is charged with presiding over all meetings of the Board and our shareholders, and
providing advice and counsel to the CEO and our company&rsquo;s other officers regarding our business and operations, as well
as focusing on oversight and governance matters.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">By separating the roles of CEO and
Chairman, our CEO is able to focus his time and energy on managing Walmart&rsquo;s complex daily operations, while our
Chairman can devote his time and attention to addressing matters relating to the responsibilities of our Board. Our CEO and
Chairman have an excellent working relationship, and, with more than 40 years of experience with Walmart, our Chairman is
well positioned to provide our CEO with guidance, advice, and counsel regarding our company&rsquo;s business, operations, and
strategy. Moreover, we believe that having a separate Chairman focused on oversight and governance matters allows the Board
to more effectively perform its risk oversight role as described below. In connection with the Board&rsquo;s annual
self-evaluation process, as required by our Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Board evaluates its organization and
processes to ensure that the Board is functioning effectively. For the foregoing reasons, we believe that our separate
CEO/Chairman structure is the most appropriate and effective leadership structure for our company and our shareholders.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Presiding Director.</I> </B>Walmart
is committed to the independence of our Board. Pursuant to the company&rsquo;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Independent
Directors, upon recommendation of the CNGC, annually appoint an independent presiding director who presides over executive sessions
of the Outside Directors and Independent Directors. Our Board has had an independent presiding director since 2004, and James
I. Cash, Jr. currently serves as the presiding director. Reflecting Walmart&rsquo;s commitment to ensuring that our Board acts
independently of management, the Board recently amended the company&rsquo;s Corporate Governance Guidelines to expand and further
clarify and formalize additional authority and responsibilities of the presiding director, including:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">serving as a liaison between the Chairman of the Board and the Independent Directors; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">approving Board meeting agendas, schedules, and Board meeting-related information; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">authority to call meetings of the directors, including separate meetings of the Outside Directors and Independent Directors; and </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">being available, when appropriate, for consultation with major shareholders (generally defined as holders of 2 percent or more of Walmart&rsquo;s outstanding Shares).</font></td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">For additional information regarding Dr.
Cash, see page 12.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>33</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 33 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta014"></A>The Board&rsquo;s Role
in Risk Oversight</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>
<DIV STYLE="padding: 5pt; border: Black 1px solid; width: 99%; background-color: rgb(216,228,228)">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The Board oversees the company&rsquo;s risk management.</font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The Board committees, which meet regularly and report to the full Board, play active roles in fulfilling the risk oversight function.</font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The company&rsquo;s management is responsible for day-to-day management of risk and is guided by robust internal processes and strong internal controls.</font></td></tr>
</table>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Taking reasonable and responsible risks is
an inherent part of Walmart&rsquo;s business, just as it is with any business, and is critical to our continued innovation, growth,
and achievement of our strategic objectives. In order to ensure the long-term success and financial strength of our company, the
Board and the Board committees play an active role in overseeing the management of risks that could potentially impact the company&rsquo;s
operations. Such risks could include operational, legal, regulatory, financial, reputational, and other risks. The Board does not
view risk in isolation, but instead considers risk in connection with virtually every business decision it makes and as part of
the company&rsquo;s approach to its business strategy. The company has robust internal processes and a strong internal control
environment that facilitate the identification and management of risk by the company&rsquo;s management, the Board, and the Board
committees.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Board carries out its risk oversight
function both as a whole and through delegation of certain risk management responsibilities to the Board committees, which report
regularly to the Board. The Audit Committee is responsible for reviewing and discussing with management the company&rsquo;s risk
identification, risk assessment, and risk management processes and policies, including the company&rsquo;s enterprise-wide risk
management program, as well as the company&rsquo;s financial and other risk exposures and the steps management has taken to monitor
and control such exposures, including the ongoing enhancement of Walmart&rsquo;s global compliance program. The Audit Committee
is also responsible for discussing with management and advising the Board with respect to the company&rsquo;s policies, processes,
and procedures regarding compliance with applicable laws and regulations, the company&rsquo;s Statement of Ethics, and the company&rsquo;s
Code of Ethics for the CEO and Senior Financial Officers. Further, the Audit Committee oversees, and receives regular reports from
management regarding, the company&rsquo;s information technology and data security programs and processes, including security measures
designed to protect information about our customers and other third parties. The Audit Committee meets regularly with the company&rsquo;s
CEO, CFO, global chief compliance officer, global chief ethics officer, and other appropriate members of management regarding the
implementation and effectiveness of the company&rsquo;s compliance and ethics programs. In addition, the Audit Committee oversees
internal investigatory matters, including the ongoing internal investigation into alleged violations of the FCPA and other alleged
crimes or misconduct in connection with certain foreign subsidiaries, and oversees the continuing enhancements to Walmart&rsquo;s
global compliance program.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The other Board committees also play a significant
role in the Board&rsquo;s oversight of risk. For example, the CNGC is charged with developing and recommending to the Board the
corporate governance principles applicable to the company; implementing incentive compensation programs with features that mitigate
risk without diminishing the incentive nature of the compensation; reviewing and assessing the company&rsquo;s compliance with
the corporate governance requirements established by the NYSE, the requirements established under SOX and the Dodd-Frank Wall Street
Reform and Consumer Protection Act and related SEC rules and regulations, and other applicable corporate governance laws and regulations;
reviewing and advising the Board and management regarding the company&rsquo;s reputation with external constituencies, the company&rsquo;s
social, community, sustainability, and charitable giving initiatives and strategies; and reviewing and advising management regarding
the company&rsquo;s legislative affairs and public policy engagement strategy. Furthermore, the SPFC regularly reviews with management
the company&rsquo;s financial status and advises management and the Board regarding financial matters, including the company&rsquo;s
global financial policies and practices, the company&rsquo;s capital structure and capital expenditures, annual financial plans,
dividend policy, and matters pertaining to potential acquisitions and divestitures. The CNGC&rsquo;s and the SPFC&rsquo;s review
of these matters necessarily includes an analysis of any risks associated with such matters. Additional information regarding the
roles and responsibilities of our Board committees can be found under &ldquo;Board Committees&rdquo; beginning on page 25.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">When a Board committee receives an update
on a risk-related matter, the chair of the relevant Board committee reports on the discussion to the full Board during the Board
committee reports portion of the next Board meeting. The open communication between the company&rsquo;s management and the Board
and the Board committees, and between the Board and the chairs and the other members of the Board committees, enables the Board,
Board committees, and management to coordinate the risk oversight role in a manner that serves the long-term interests of the company
and our shareholders.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>34</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 34 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta015"></A>Oversight of the Company&rsquo;s
Legislative Affairs and Public Policy Engagement Strategy</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Walmart participates in the political process
when we believe that doing so will serve the best interests of the company and our shareholders. Walmart is committed to engaging
in the political process as a good corporate citizen and in a manner that complies with all applicable laws. Over the years, Walmart
has provided greater transparency regarding the company&rsquo;s political engagement. Consistent with our commitment to participating
in the political process in a thoughtful and compliant manner, in fiscal 2014, the Board amended the charter of the CNGC, requiring
the CNGC to review and advise management regarding the company&rsquo;s legislative affairs and public policy engagement strategy.
Similarly, pursuant to its charter, the CNGC is further responsible for reviewing and advising management regarding the company&rsquo;s
charitable giving strategy and the company&rsquo;s social, community, and sustainability initiatives. For additional information
regarding Walmart&rsquo;s engagement in the political process, please see Walmart&rsquo;s Global Responsibility Report, available
at <I>http://corporate.walmart.com/global-responsibility/,</I> as well as Walmart&rsquo;s Government Relations Policy, available
at <I>http://corporate.walmart.com/government-relations-policy.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta016"></A>Management Development
and Succession Planning</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Our Board has a thorough process in place
regarding senior management development and succession planning. The CNGC has primary responsibility for reviewing and establishing
for the full Board&rsquo;s approval the succession planning and retention practices for our Executive Officers and other senior
leaders. Executive Officer succession planning and senior management development is a regular topic on the agendas for the meetings
of the CNGC. At these meetings, the members of our CNGC, in consultation with our CEO, our Executive Vice President, Global People,
and others as the CNGC may deem appropriate, engage in comprehensive deliberations regarding the development and evaluation of
current and potential senior leaders, as well as the development of executive succession plans, including succession plans for
our CEO position. The Board, upon recommendation of the CNGC, has also separately developed a CEO succession planning process to
address certain unanticipated events and emergency situations.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">After serving as our CEO for five years,
Michael T. Duke retired from that position effective January 31, 2014. Pursuant to the CNGC&rsquo;s and the Board&rsquo;s robust
succession planning process described above, the Board appointed C. Douglas McMillon to succeed Mr. Duke as our CEO effective February
1, 2014. Mr. McMillon was also appointed to the Board effective November 22, 2013. Mr. Duke continues to serve as Chairman of the
Executive Committee of the Board, and in that capacity, he, among other things, provides advice and counsel to Mr. McMillon, as
requested, to help ensure a smooth transition in the CEO role. Mr. McMillon joined Walmart in 1990 as an assistant store manager,
and since that time, he has held numerous leadership positions in our company, including Executive Vice President, President and
CEO, Walmart International, and Executive Vice President, President and CEO, Sam&rsquo;s Club. For additional information regarding
Mr. McMillon, see page 17.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta017"></A>Board and Committee Evaluations</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Each year, the Board and each Board committee
conduct a self-evaluation by means of extensive written questionnaires completed by each director and committee member. These anonymous
questionnaires are administered by a third party and are designed to elicit candid feedback regarding the effectiveness of the
Board and Board committees, Board and Board committee structure and dynamics, and areas where the Board and Board committees could
improve their effectiveness.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">In fiscal 2014, we further enhanced our Board
and Board committee evaluation process by supplementing the written questionnaires with confidential one-on-one interviews of our
directors conducted by an independent, third-party expert, who works with our Chairman and the Chair of the CNGC to develop suggested
action plans. The full Board and each Board committee discuss the results of these evaluations at their next meetings.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>35</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 35 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta018"></A>Board Attendance at Annual
Shareholders&rsquo; Meetings</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The
Board has adopted a policy stating that all directors are expected to attend the company&rsquo;s annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings.
While the Board understands that there may be situations that prevent a director from attending an annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting,
the Board encourages all directors to make attendance at all annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings a</FONT> <FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">priority.
Each of the 14 individuals nominated by the Board for election to the Board at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting attended
the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. In addition, Mr. Scott and Mr. Williams, as well as Ms. Burns, who did not stand for
reelection at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, attended that meeting.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta019"></A>Communications with the
Board</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Board welcomes communications from shareholders
and other interested parties and believes that such communications are an important part of our corporate governance practices.
Therefore, we provide shareholders and other interested parties with a number of methods for communicating with the Board or individual
directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Shareholders and other interested parties
may write to the Board or individual members of the Board at:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 54pt"><IMG SRC="lwmtx36x1.jpg" ALT=""></td>
    <TD><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Name of Director(s) or Board of Directors<BR>
 c/o Gordon Y. Allison, Vice President and <BR>
General Counsel, Corporate Division<BR>
 Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. <BR>
702 Southwest 8<sup>th </sup>Street <BR>
Bentonville, Arkansas 72716-0215</font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</td>
    <TD>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><IMG SRC="lwmtx36x2.jpg" ALT=""></td>
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Shareholders and other interested parties</FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">also may e-mail the entire Board at </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>directors@wal-mart.com;</I></FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Independent Directors at </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>independentdirectors@wal-mart.com;</I> </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the Non-Management Directors at </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>nonmanagementdirectors@wal-mart.com;</I> and any </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">individual director, at the full name of the director </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">as listed in this proxy statement followed by </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&ldquo;@wal-mart.com.&rdquo; For example, shareholders </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">may e-mail S. Robson Walton, Chairman, at </FONT><BR>
    <FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><I>srobsonwalton@wal-mart.com.</I></FONT></td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Our company receives a large volume of correspondence
regarding a wide range of subjects each day. As a result, our individual directors are often not able to respond to all communications
directly. Therefore, our Board has established a process for managing communications to the Board and individual directors.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Communications directed to the Board or individual
directors are reviewed to determine whether, based on the facts and circumstances of the communication, a response on behalf of
the Board or an individual director is appropriate. If a response on behalf of the Board or an individual director is appropriate,
Walmart will assist the Board or individual director in gathering all relevant information and preparing a proposed response for
the Board&rsquo;s or the individual director&rsquo;s review and approval.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Communications related to day-to-day management
functions or operations are typically directed to an appropriate member of management for a response. Further, Walmart will typically
not distribute to the Board or an individual director communications of a threatening or personal nature, voluminous or mass mailings
on the same subject matter, business solicitations or advertisements, surveys, or other communications otherwise inappropriate
for the Board&rsquo;s or an individual director&rsquo;s consideration. Walmart maintains records of communications directed to
the Board and individual directors, and these records are available to our directors at any time upon request.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta020"></A><B>Shareholder Outreach and
Engagement</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The company&rsquo;s relationship with its
shareholders is a critical part of our corporate governance processes, and we recognize the value of taking their views into account.
We conduct shareholder outreach throughout the year to ensure that management and the Board understand and consider the issues
of importance to our shareholders and are able to address them appropriately. We value comments from shareholders, customers, and
others about our business, and we appreciate that we receive input from many stakeholders on a daily basis. Specifically related
to the investment community, we receive regular analysts&rsquo; reports about our business and interact from time to time with
analysts, banks, and rating agencies. This feedback helps us improve.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Our company&rsquo;s investor relations (&ldquo;IR&rdquo;)
department is the key point of contact for shareholder interaction with the company. Shareholders may access information about
our company through our website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com.</I> This website features a wide variety of information relevant
to shareholders, including recent company financial news, information regarding company events, our corporate governance documents,
our Annual Reports to Shareholders, Global Responsibility Reports, SEC reports, proxy statements, and stock information, among</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>36</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 36 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">other items. In fiscal 2014, we made enhancements
to the IR website to include a special section for investors with a particular interest in environmental, social, and governance
(&ldquo;ESG&rdquo;) matters. On this section of the IR website, shareholders and other interested parties can access updates regarding
Walmart&rsquo;s initiatives and progress on ESG matters, including archived webcasts that feature company leaders discussing various
ESG topics.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Shareholders can also contact IR through
our investor hotline at (479) 273-6463, through email at <I>wmirqa@walmart.com,</I> or through providing feedback via our IR smartphone
app, WMT IR. The Walmart IR smartphone app is free and available for iPad, iPhone, and Android devices. IR responds to inquiries
from shareholders &ndash; ranging from individuals to institutional shareholders &ndash; and conveys the company&rsquo;s position
on a wide range of issues that matter to our shareholders. When appropriate, the IR team partners with subject matter experts
from other company departments, such as legal, compliance, sustainability, operations, merchandising, and other areas to provide
additional context and insight regarding the company&rsquo;s response to a shareholder inquiry. We have had success engaging with
parties to understand shareholder concerns and reaching resolutions on issues that are in the best interests of our shareholders.
Beyond our standard means of communication, in 2013, members of management spoke at numerous industry and investment community
conferences, and we also conducted activities and events such as store tours, investor road shows, analyst meetings, investor
conferences, and the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Finally, as noted above, the Board recently amended our Corporate
Governance Guidelines to provide that the Board&rsquo;s independent presiding director will, when deemed appropriate, be available
for consultation with major shareholders.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0pt; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta022"></A>Compensation
Committee Interlocks and Insider Participation</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 10pt; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0pt; text-align: justify">None of the directors who served on the CNGC
at any time during fiscal 2014 (including the current CNGC members listed above on page 26 and Steven S Reinemund, who served on

none of the members who served on the CNGC at any time during fiscal 2014 had any relationship with our company requiring disclosure
under the section of this proxy statement entitled &ldquo;Related Person Transactions.&rdquo; Finally, no Executive Officer serves,
or in the past fiscal year has served, as a director of, or as a member of the compensation committee (or other board committee
performing equivalent functions) of, any entity that has one or more of its executive officers serving as a director of Walmart
or as a member of the CNGC.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0pt; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta023"></A>Audit Committee
Report</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 10pt; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0pt; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">The
Audit Committee consists of four Outside Directors, each of whom has been determined by the Board to meet the heightened independence
criteria applicable to Audit Committee members and to satisfy the financial literacy requirements of the NYSE Listed Company Rules
and the applicable rules of the SEC. Each member of the Audit Committee has also been determined by the Board to be an &ldquo;audit
committee financial expert&rdquo; as defined under applicable SEC rules and regulations. The members of the Audit Committee are
James I. Cash, Jr.; Pamela J. Craig; Timothy P. Flynn; and Christopher J. Williams, the Chair of the Audit Committee. Additional
information regarding the members of the Audit Committee</FONT> <FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">and the
Audit Committee&rsquo;s roles and responsibilities is set forth under &ldquo;Proposal No. 1 &ndash; Election of Directors&rdquo;
and &ldquo;Board Committees&rdquo; on pages 11 &ndash; 19 and 25 &ndash; 26 of this proxy statement.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 10pt; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 0pt; text-align: justify">The Audit Committee held 22 meetings in fiscal
2014, 13 of which related primarily to its ongoing FCPA-related investigation and compliance matters. Additional information about
the Audit Committee&rsquo;s role in the investigation may be found under &ldquo;Compensation of the Directors&rdquo; on page 28.
During fiscal 2014, at its regularly scheduled in-person meetings, the Audit Committee had separate private sessions with our company&rsquo;s</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0 0pt 10pt; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">CEO, CFO, chief audit executive, global chief

auditors. The Audit Committee has retained independent legal counsel and met periodically with its legal counsel throughout fiscal

<I>http://stock.walmart.com/corporate-governance/governance-documents.</I> The Audit Committee reviews and assesses the adequacy
of its charter on an annual basis.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><A NAME="lwmta024"></A><B>Audit Committee Financial
Experts</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(28,145,255)">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Board has determined that James I. Cash,
Jr., Pamela J. Craig, Timothy P. Flynn, and Christopher J. Williams are &ldquo;audit committee financial experts&rdquo; as that
term is defined in Item 407(d)(5)(ii) of Regulation S-K of the SEC, and that all members of the Audit Committee are &ldquo;independent&rdquo;
under Section 10A(m)(3) of the Exchange Act, the SEC&rsquo;s Rule 10A-3, and the requirements set forth in the NYSE Listed Company
Rules.</P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 38 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta025"></A>Audit Committee Pre-Approval
Policy</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">To ensure the independence of our independent
accountants and to comply with applicable securities laws, the NYSE Listed Company Rules, and the Audit Committee charter, the
Audit Committee is responsible for reviewing, deliberating on, and, if appropriate, pre-approving all audit, audit-related, and
non-audit services to be performed for our company by the independent accountants. For that purpose, the Audit Committee has established
a policy and related procedures regarding the pre-approval of all audit, audit-related, and non-audit services to be performed
by our company&rsquo;s independent accountants (the &ldquo;Pre-Approval Policy&rdquo;).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Pre-Approval Policy provides that our
company&rsquo;s independent accountants may not perform any audit, audit-related, or non-audit service for Walmart, subject to
those exceptions that may be permitted by applicable law, unless: (i) the service has been pre-approved by the Audit Committee;
or (ii) Walmart engaged the independent accountants to perform the service pursuant to the pre-approval provisions of the Pre-Approval
Policy. In addition, the Pre-Approval Policy prohibits the Audit Committee from pre-approving certain non-audit services that are
prohibited from being performed by our company&rsquo;s independent accountants by applicable securities laws. The Pre-Approval
Policy also provides that Walmart&rsquo;s corporate controller will periodically update the Audit Committee as to services provided
by the independent accountants. With respect to each such service, the independent accountants provide detailed back-up documentation
to the corporate controller.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Pursuant
to the Pre-Approval Policy, the Audit Committee has pre-approved certain categories of services to be performed by the independent
accountants and a maximum amount of fees for each category. The Audit Committee annually</FONT> <FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">reassesses
these service categories and the associated fees. Individual projects within the approved service categories have been pre-approved
only to the extent that the fees for each individual project do not exceed a specified dollar limit, which amount is reassessed
annually. Projects within a pre-approved service category with fees in excess of the specified fee limit for individual projects
may not proceed without the specific prior approval of the Audit Committee (or a member to whom pre-approval authority has been
delegated). In addition, no project within a pre-approved service category will be considered to have been pre-approved by the
Audit Committee if the project would cause the maximum amount of fees for the service category to be exceeded, and the project
may only proceed with the prior approval of the Audit Committee (or a member to whom pre-approval authority has been delegated)
to increase the aggregate amount of fees for the service category.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">At least annually, the Audit Committee designates
a member of the Audit Committee to whom it delegates its pre-approval responsibilities. That member has the authority to approve
interim requests as set forth above within the defined, pre-approved service categories, as well as interim requests to engage
Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants for services outside the Audit Committee&rsquo;s pre-approved service categories. The member
has the authority to pre-approve any audit, audit-related, or non-audit service that falls outside the pre-approved service categories,
provided that the member determines that the service would not compromise the independent accountants&rsquo; independence and the
member informs the Audit Committee of his or her decision at the Audit Committee&rsquo;s next regular meeting. The Audit Committee
approved all of the audit-related fees, tax fees, and all other fees paid to the company&rsquo;s independent accountants in fiscal
2014.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta026"></A>Transaction Review Policy</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; ">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Board has adopted a written policy (the
&ldquo;Transaction Review Policy&rdquo;) applicable to: all Walmart officers who serve as Executive Vice Presidents or above; all
directors and director nominees; all shareholders beneficially owning more than five percent of Walmart&rsquo;s outstanding Shares;
and the immediate family members of each of the preceding persons (collectively, the &ldquo;Covered Persons&rdquo;). Any entity
in which a Covered Person has a direct or indirect material financial interest or of which a Covered Person is an officer or holds
a significant management position (each a &ldquo;Covered Entity&rdquo;) is also covered by the policy. The Transaction Review Policy
applies to any transaction or series of similar or related transactions in which a Covered Person or Covered Entity has a direct
or indirect material financial interest and in which Walmart is a participant (each, a &ldquo;Covered Transaction&rdquo;).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Under
the Transaction Review Policy, each Covered Person is responsible for reporting to Walmart&rsquo;s chief audit executive</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">any Covered Transactions of which he or she has knowledge. Walmart&rsquo;s
chief audit executive, with the assistance of other appropriate Walmart personnel, reviews each Covered Transaction and submits
the results of such review to the Audit Committee. The Audit Committee reviews each Covered Transaction and either approves or
disapproves the transaction. To approve a Covered Transaction, the Audit Committee must find that:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the substantive terms and negotiation of the Covered Transaction are fair to Walmart and its shareholders and the substantive terms are no less favorable to Walmart and its shareholders than those in similar transactions negotiated at an arm&rsquo;s-length basis; and </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">if the Covered Person is a director or officer of Walmart, he or she has otherwise complied with the terms of Walmart&rsquo;s Statement of Ethics as it applies to the Covered Transaction.</font></td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><I>&nbsp;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>39</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 39 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Audit Committee may also ratify a Covered
Transaction of which prior approval and review was not sought if the Audit Committee determines that the Covered Transaction meets
the criteria above and the failure to obtain pre-approval was unintentional or inadvertent.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The following categories of transactions
are exempt from review and approval under the Transaction Review Policy:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">transactions that involve a monetary value of less than $120,000; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">transactions that result from a competitive bid process; </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">ordinary banking transactions; and </font></td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><font style="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">any series of substantially similar transactions after the Audit Committee has reviewed and approved a single transaction of that type as meeting the requirements of the policy.</font></td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; ">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 18pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta027"></A>Related Person Transactions</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; ">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">This section discusses certain direct and
indirect relationships and transactions involving Walmart and certain of its directors, Executive Officers, the beneficial owners
of more than five percent of the Shares outstanding, and certain immediate family members of the foregoing. Walmart believes that
the terms of the transactions described below are comparable to terms that would have been reached by unrelated parties in arm&rsquo;s-length
transactions.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&bull;</FONT></td>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 180pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B><A NAME="lwmta028"></A>Proposal No. 2</B></td>
    <TD>Ratification of Independent Accountants</td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Although shareholder ratification is not
required, the appointment of E&amp;Y as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2015 is being submitted for ratification
at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting because the Board believes doing so is a matter of good corporate governance practice.
Furthermore, the Audit Committee will take the shareholders&rsquo; vote on this matter into consideration in future deliberations.
If E&amp;Y&rsquo;s selection is not ratified at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, the Audit Committee will consider
the engagement of other independent accountants. The Audit Committee may terminate E&amp;Y&rsquo;s engagement as the company&rsquo;s
independent accountants without the approval of the company&rsquo;s shareholders whenever the Audit Committee deems termination
appropriate.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Audit Committee is directly responsible
for the appointment, compensation, retention, and oversight of the independent accountants. The Audit Committee has appointed E&amp;Y
as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants to audit the consolidated financial statements of the company for fiscal 2015. E&amp;Y
and its predecessor, Arthur Young &amp; Company, have been Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants since prior to the company&rsquo;s
initial offering of securities to the public in 1970. E&amp;Y served as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal
2014 and audited and reported on the company&rsquo;s annual consolidated financial statements for that year.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The Audit Committee annually reviews E&amp;Y&rsquo;s
independence and performance in determining whether to retain E&amp;Y or engage another independent registered public accounting
firm as our company&rsquo;s independent accountants. As part of that annual review, the Audit Committee considers, among other
things, the following:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; color: rgb(0,102,204)">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">The quality and efficiency of the current and historical services provided to our company by E&amp;Y,
    including the results of an annual internal survey of key global financial management; </td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">E&amp;Y&rsquo;s capability and expertise in handling the breadth and complexity of our company&rsquo;s global operations;
    </td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt">External data on E&amp;Y&rsquo;s audit quality and performance obtained from recent Public Company Accounting Oversight
    Board reports regarding E&amp;Y; </td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">E&amp;Y&rsquo;s independence from our company; </td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt">The appropriateness of E&amp;Y&rsquo;s fees; and </td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="color: rgb(0,102,204); padding-top: 3pt">&bull;</td>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt">E&amp;Y&rsquo;s tenure as our company&rsquo;s independent accountants, including the benefits of having a long-tenured
    auditor.</td></tr>
</table>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Based on this evaluation, the Audit Committee
believes that E&amp;Y is independent and well qualified to serve as our company&rsquo;s independent accountants. Further, the Audit
Committee and the Board believe it is in the best interests of Walmart and our company&rsquo;s shareholders to retain E&amp;Y as
our company&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2015.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>41</B></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 41 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0">Representatives of E&amp;Y
will attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. They will have the opportunity to make a statement if they desire to do
so and to respond to appropriate questions.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">E&amp;Y&rsquo;s fees billed for fiscal 2014
and fiscal 2013 were as follows:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">A description of the types of services provided
in each category is as follows:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Audit Fees</I> &ndash; Includes the audit
of the company&rsquo;s annual consolidated financial statements, the audit of the effectiveness of internal control over financial
reporting, the review of the company&rsquo;s quarterly reports on Form 10-Q, statutory audits required internationally, and consents
for and review of registration statements filed with the SEC.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Audit-Related Fees</I> &ndash; Includes
audits of the company&rsquo;s employee benefit plans, due diligence in connection with acquisitions, accounting consultations
related to GAAP, the application of GAAP to proposed transactions, statutory financial statement audits of non-consolidated affiliates,
and work related to the company&rsquo;s compliance with its obligations under SOX.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Tax Fees</I> &ndash; Includes tax compliance
at international locations, domestic and international tax advice and planning, assistance with tax audits and appeals, and tax
planning for acquisitions and restructurings.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">None of the services described above were
approved pursuant to the de <I>minimis</I> exception provided in Rule 2-01(c)(7)(i)(C) of Regulation S-X promulgated by the SEC.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0,102,204)"><B>For the above reasons,
the Board recommends that the shareholders vote FOR the ratification of E&amp;Y as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants
for fiscal 2015.</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>42</B></P>
