<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">4.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">Who counts the votes? Are my votes confidential?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Broadridge will count the votes. The
Board has appointed two employees of Broadridge as the inspectors of election. Your proxy card or ballot and voting records
(including with respect to votes cast by phone or mobile device or over the internet) will not be disclosed unless the law
requires disclosure, you request disclosure, or your vote is cast in a contested election. If you write comments on your
proxy card or ballot, your comments will be provided to Walmart by Broadridge, but how you voted&nbsp;will remain
confidential.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">5.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: left">What is the quorum requirement for holding the 2014 Annual
    Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The holders of a majority of the Shares outstanding and entitled
to vote as of the record date for the meeting must be present in person or represented by proxy for business to be transacted at
the meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">6.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; text-align: left">What vote is required to elect a director at the 2014
    Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">To be elected in an &ldquo;uncontested
election&rdquo; of directors, which under our Bylaws is an election in which the number of nominees for director is not
greater than the number of directors to be elected, a director nominee must receive affirmative votes representing a majority
of the votes cast by the holders of Shares present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on
the election of directors (a &ldquo;majority&nbsp;vote&rdquo;). To be elected in a &ldquo;contested election&rdquo; of
directors, which our Bylaws define as an election in which the number of nominees for director is greater than the number of
directors to be elected, a director nominee must receive a plurality of the votes of the holders of Shares present in person
or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on the election of directors. We expect the election of directors
at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting to be an uncontested election.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">7.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">What happens if a director nominee fails to receive a majority vote in an uncontested election at the
    2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Any incumbent director who is a
director nominee and who does not receive a majority vote must promptly tender his or her offer of resignation as a director
for consideration by the Board. Each director standing for reelection at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting has
agreed to resign, effective upon acceptance of such resignation by the Board, if he or she does not receive a majority vote.
The Board must accept or reject such resignation within 90 days following certification of the shareholder vote in accordance
with the procedures established by the Bylaws. If a director&rsquo;s resignation offer is not accepted by the Board, that
director will continue to serve until our company&rsquo;s next annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting and his or her successor is
duly elected and qualified or until the director&rsquo;s earlier death, resignation, or removal.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Any director nominee who is not an incumbent director and who
fails to receive a majority vote in an uncontested election will not be elected as a director, and a vacancy will be left on the
Board. The Board, in its sole discretion, may either fill a vacancy resulting from a director nominee not receiving a majority
vote pursuant to the Bylaws or decrease the size of the Board to eliminate the vacancy.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>8.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>What vote is required to pass
    the other proposals at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the
Shares present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on the proposal at issue is required
for: (i) the ratification of the appointment of E&amp;Y as Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2015; (ii) the
adoption of a non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; and (iii) the adoption
of each of the shareholder proposals.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>84</B></P>


<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 84 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>9.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>What is the effect of an &ldquo;abstain&rdquo;
    vote or a &ldquo;broker non-vote&rdquo; on the proposals to be voted on at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Abstentions.</I> </B>A Share voted &ldquo;abstain&rdquo;
with respect to any proposal is considered as present and entitled to vote with respect to that proposal, but is not considered
a vote cast with respect to that proposal. Therefore, an abstention will not have any effect on the election of directors. Because
each of the other proposals requires the affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the Shares present and entitled to vote
on each such proposal in order to pass, an abstention will have the effect of a vote against each of the other proposals.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Broker Non-Votes.</I> </B>A &ldquo;broker non-vote&rdquo;
occurs if your Shares are not registered in your name (that is, you hold your Shares in &ldquo;street name&rdquo;) and you do not
provide the record holder of your Shares (usually a bank, broker, or other nominee) with voting instructions on any matter as to
which, under the NYSE rules for member organizations (such as brokers), a broker may not vote without instructions from you, but
the broker nevertheless provides a proxy for your Shares. Shares as to which a broker non-vote occurs are considered present for
purposes of determining whether a quorum exists, but are not considered &ldquo;votes cast&rdquo; or Shares &ldquo;entitled to vote&rdquo;
with respect to a voting matter. Therefore, a broker non-vote will not have any effect on the outcome of the proposals.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Under the NYSE rules for member organizations: (i) the election
of directors; (ii) the non-binding advisory vote to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; and (iii) each of the
shareholder proposals described in this proxy statement are not matters on which a broker may vote without your instructions. Therefore,
if your Shares are not registered in your name and you do not provide instructions to the record holder of your Shares regarding
these proposals, a broker non-vote as to your Shares will result with respect to these proposals. The ratification of the appointment
of independent accountants is a routine item under the NYSE rules for member organizations. As a result, brokers who do not receive
instructions from you as to how to vote on that matter generally may vote your Shares on that matter in their discretion.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If your Shares are held of record by a bank, broker, or other
nominee, we urge you to give instructions to your bank, broker, or other nominee as to how you wish your Shares to be voted so
you may participate in the shareholder voting on these important matters.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC">10.</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: bold 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid">How do I vote?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0pt">The process for voting your Shares depends on how your Shares
are held. Generally, as discussed above, you may hold Shares as a &ldquo;record holder&rdquo; (that is, in your own name) or in
&ldquo;street&nbsp;name&rdquo; (that is, through a nominee, such as a broker or bank). As explained above, if you hold Shares in
&ldquo;street name,&rdquo; you are considered to be the &ldquo;beneficial owner&rdquo; of those Shares.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Voting by Record Holders.</I> </B>If
you are a record holder, you may vote by proxy or you may vote in person at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. If you
are a record holder and would like to vote your Shares by proxy prior to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, you have
four ways to vote:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 60pt; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><IMG SRC="lwmtx85x1.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 8pt; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">go to the website <I>www.proxyvote.com</I> and follow the instructions
    at that website;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><IMG SRC="lwmtx85x2.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">scan the QR code on your proxy card or notice of availability with your mobile device and follow the instructions provided;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><IMG SRC="lwmtx85x3.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">call 1-800-690-6903 using a touch-tone phone (toll&nbsp;charges may apply for calls made from outside the&nbsp;United
    States) and follow the instructions provided on the call; or</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: left"><IMG SRC="lwmtx85x4.jpg" ALT=""></TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">if you received a proxy card in the mail, complete, sign, date, and mail the proxy card in the return envelope provided
    to you.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>



<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Please note that telephone and
internet voting will close at 11:59 p.m. Eastern time on June 5, 2014. If you wish to vote by telephone or internet, follow
the instructions on your proxy card (if you received a paper copy of the proxy materials) or in the notice of availability of
the proxy materials. If you received a proxy card in the mail and wish to vote by completing and returning the proxy card via
mail, please note that your completed proxy card must be received before the polls close for voting at the 2014 Annual
Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If you plan to attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting
and wish to vote in person, you will be given, upon your request, a ballot at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Even
if you vote by proxy prior to June 6, 2014, you may still attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Voting by Beneficial Owners of Shares
Held in &ldquo;Street Name.&rdquo;</I> </B>If your Shares are held in the name of a broker, bank, or other nominee (that is, your
Shares are held in &ldquo;street name&rdquo;), you should receive separate instructions from the record holder of your Shares
describing how to vote. Nonetheless, if your Shares are held in the name of a broker, bank, or other nominee and you want to vote
in person, you will need to obtain (and bring with you to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting) a legal proxy from the
record holder of your Shares (who must have been the record holder of your Shares as of the close of business on April 11, 2014)
indicating that you were a beneficial owner of Shares as of the close of business on April 11, 2014, as well as the number of
Shares of which you were the beneficial owner on the record date, and appointing you as the record holder&rsquo;s proxy to vote
the Shares covered by that proxy at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>85</B></P>


<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 85 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

    <P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Voting of Shares Held in the 401(k)
Plan or the Wal-Mart Puerto Rico 401(k) Plan.</I> </B>If your Shares are held through the 401(k) Plan or the Wal-Mart Puerto Rico
401(k) Plan, you must provide instructions on how you wish to vote your Shares held through such plans no later than 11:59 p.m.
Eastern time on June 3, 2014. If you do not provide such instructions by that time, your Shares will be voted by the Retirement
Plans Committee of the respective plan in accordance with the rules of the applicable plan.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>11.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>What if I do not specify a choice for a proposal when returning
    a proxy or a voting instruction form?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">We urge all shareholders to express their
choices on each voting matter described on the proxy card or the voting instruction form (which you will receive from your broker,
bank, or other nominee, if your Shares are held in &ldquo;street name&rdquo;).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Shares Owned by Record Holders.</I>
</B>If you are a record owner of Shares and you sign and return a proxy card, unless you indicate otherwise, the persons named
as proxies on the proxy card will vote your Shares: FOR the election of each of the nominees for director named in this proxy
statement; FOR the ratification of E&amp;Y as Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2015; FOR the non-binding advisory
resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; and AGAINST each of the shareholder proposals appearing in
this proxy statement.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Shares Held in &ldquo;Street Name&rdquo;
by Beneficial Owners.</I> </B>If you are a beneficial owner of Shares held in &ldquo;street name&rdquo; and you sign and return
a voting instruction form to your bank, broker, or other nominee (in accordance with the voting instructions provided by such
bank, broker, or other nominee), but do not provide instructions regarding how you wish your Shares to be voted on each of the
voting matters described in this proxy statement, as more specifically discussed in the answer to Question No. 9 above, a &ldquo;broker
non-vote&rdquo; will result with respect to your Shares regarding the election of each of the nominees for director named in this
proxy statement; the non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; and each of the
shareholder proposals appearing in this proxy statement. Banks, brokers, and other nominees who do not receive instructions from
you regarding the ratification of the appointment of independent accountants may generally vote on that matter in their discretion.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>12.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>I completed and returned my proxy card, but I have changed
    my mind about how I want to vote. Can I revoke my proxy and change my vote?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Yes, if you are a record holder, you may
revoke a previously submitted proxy and change your vote by:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">delivering a written notice of revocation to Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Secretary at the address provided in the Notice of 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting included in this proxy statement before the polls close for voting at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting; </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">signing a proxy bearing a later date than the proxy being revoked and delivering it to Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Secretary at the address provided in the Notice of 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting included in this proxy statement before the polls close for voting at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting; or </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">voting in person at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If your Shares are held in street name through
a broker, bank, or other nominee, you should contact the record holder of your Shares regarding how to revoke your voting instructions.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>13.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>Why did I receive a notice regarding the internet availability
    of the proxy materials instead of a paper copy of the proxy materials?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Important Notice Regarding the Availability
of Proxy Materials for the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</I> </B>This year, we are again taking advantage of the rules
of the SEC that allow us to furnish our proxy materials over the internet. As a result, we are mailing a notice of availability
of the proxy materials on the internet, rather than a full paper set of the proxy materials, to many of our shareholders. This
notice of availability includes instructions on how to access our proxy materials on the internet, as well as instructions on
how shareholders may obtain a paper copy of the proxy materials by mail or a printable copy electronically. Shareholders who have
affirmatively requested electronic delivery of our proxy materials will receive instructions via e-mail regarding how to access
these materials electronically. All other shareholders, including shareholders who have previously requested to receive a paper
copy of the materials, will receive a full paper set of the proxy materials by mail. This distribution process will contribute
to our sustainability efforts and will reduce the costs of printing and distributing our proxy materials.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>86</B></p>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 86 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>14.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>How can I access the proxy materials over the internet?
    How can I elect to receive proxy materials for future annual meetings electronically? How can I request a paper copy of the
    proxy materials?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Accessing the Proxy Materials on the
Internet.</I> </B>You can access the proxy statement and the Annual Report to Shareholders in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo; section
of Walmart&rsquo;s corporate website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports.</I> In accordance with the rules of the SEC,
we do not use software that identifies visitors accessing our proxy materials on our website.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Electing to Receive Proxy Materials
for Future Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meetings Electronically.</I> </B>If you wish to join in Walmart&rsquo;s sustainability efforts,
you can instruct Walmart to deliver its proxy materials for future annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings to you electronically by
e-mail. If you choose to access future proxy materials electronically, you will receive an e-mail with instructions containing
a link to the website where those materials are available and a link to the proxy voting website. Your election to access proxy
materials electronically will remain in effect until you terminate it. You may choose this method of delivery in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo;
section of Walmart&rsquo;s corporate website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports.</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Obtaining a Paper Copy of the Proxy
Materials.</I> </B>If you received a notice regarding the internet availability of the proxy materials, you will find instructions
about how to obtain a paper copy of the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders in your notice. If you received
an e-mail notification as to the availability of the proxy materials, you will find instructions about how to obtain a paper copy
of the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders as part of that e-mail notification. We will mail a paper copy of
the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders to all shareholders to whom we do not send a notice of availability
or an e-mail notification regarding the internet availability of the proxy materials.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>15.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>What should I do if I receive more than one notice of,
    or e-mail notification about, the internet availability of the proxy materials or more than one paper copy of the proxy materials?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Some shareholders may receive more than one
notice of internet availability, more than one e-mail notification, or more than one paper copy of the proxy materials, including
multiple proxy cards. For example, if you hold your Shares in more than one brokerage account, you may receive a separate notice
of availability, a separate e-mail notification, or a separate voting instruction form for each brokerage account in which you
hold Shares. If you are a shareholder of record and your Shares are registered in more than one name, you may receive a separate
notice of availability, a separate e-mail notification, or a separate set of paper proxy materials and proxy card for each name
in which you hold Shares. To vote all of your Shares, you must complete, sign, date, and return each proxy card you receive or
vote the Shares to which each proxy card relates by telephone, internet, or mobile device as described above, or vote in person
as described above. If you have Shares held in one or more &ldquo;street names,&rdquo; you must complete, sign, date, and return
to each bank, broker, or other nominee through which you hold Shares each voting instruction form received from that bank, broker,
or other nominee (or obtain a proxy from each such nominee holder if you wish to vote in person at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo;
Meeting).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>16.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><B>What is householding and how can I opt-out or enroll?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If you are a beneficial owner of Shares,
your bank, broker, or other nominee may deliver a single set of proxy materials to any household at which two or more shareholders
reside unless contrary instructions have been received from you. This procedure, referred to as householding, reduces the volume
of duplicate materials shareholders receive and reduces mailing expenses. Shareholders may revoke their consent to future householding
mailings or enroll in householding by contacting their bank, broker, or other nominee. Alternatively, if you wish to receive a
separate set of proxy materials for the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, we will deliver them promptly upon request made
in accordance with the instructions described in the answer to Question 14 above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>87</B></p>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 87 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">
    <TD STYLE="width: 36pt; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>17.</B></FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; text-align: left"><B>How can I attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
    What do I need to bring?</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>



<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0" STYLE="width: 99%; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 10pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: White">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="text-align: center; padding: 10pt; width: 10%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: center; padding: 10pt; background-color: rgb(0,102,204); width: 80%"><B>IMPORTANT NOTICE: If you plan to attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting in person, you must follow the instructions below
to gain admission.</B></TD>
    <TD STYLE="width: 10%; padding: 10pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE>






<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>Only shareholders who owned Shares
as of the close of business on April 11, 2014 are entitled to attend the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</I> </B>You
will be admitted to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting only if you present valid proof of Share ownership as described
below and photo identification (such as a valid driver&rsquo;s license or passport) at an entrance to Bud Walton Arena, the facility
at which the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting is to be held.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">If your Shares are registered in your name and you received your proxy materials by mail, you should bring the proxy statement you received in the mail or the proxy card that you received in the mail (or, if you have already completed and returned your proxy card, the top part of the proxy card marked &ldquo;keep this portion for your records&rdquo;) to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">If your Shares are registered in your name and you received a notice of internet availability of the proxy materials in the mail, you should bring that notice of internet availability with you to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">If you received an e-mail with instructions containing a link to the website where our proxy materials are available and a link to the proxy voting website, bring that e-mail with you to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">If you are a beneficial owner of Shares and your Shares are held in street name as described above, you will be admitted to the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting only if you present either a valid legal proxy from your bank, broker, or other nominee as to your Shares, the notice of internet availability of the proxy materials (if you received one), a voting instruction form that you received from your bank, broker, or other nominee (if you have not already completed and returned the voting instruction form), or a recent bank, brokerage, or other statement showing that you owned Shares as of the close of business on April 11, 2014.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>The use of cameras, camcorders, videotaping
equipment, and other recording devices will not be permitted in Bud Walton Arena. Attendees may not bring into the arena large
packages or other material that could pose a safety or disruption hazard (e.g., fireworks, noisemakers, horns, confetti, etc.).
</I></B>Photographs and videos taken at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting may be used by Walmart. By attending the 2014
Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, you will be agreeing to Walmart&rsquo;s use of those photographs and waive any claim or rights
with respect to those photographs and videos and their use.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt; text-align: left; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>18.</B></FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>I am unable to attend the meeting in person. Can I view the meeting via webcast?</B></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Yes. If you are unable to attend the 2014
Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting in person, we invite you to view a live webcast of the meeting at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports.
</I>The webcast of the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting will be available for viewing on our corporate website for a limited
time after the meeting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse; font: 14pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 36pt; text-align: left; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><FONT STYLE="color: #0066CC"><B>19.</B></FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify; border-bottom: rgb(0,102,204) 2px solid"><B>When will the company announce the voting results?</B></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">We will announce the outcome of each proposal
voted on at the 2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting at the conclusion of that meeting. We will report the preliminary voting
results in a press release on or before June 9, 2014, which will be available on our corporate website, and report the official
voting results in a Current Report on Form 8-K filed with the SEC on or before June&nbsp;12, 2014.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>88</B></p>

<P STYLE="font: 22pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta051"></A>SUBMISSION OF SHAREHOLDER
PROPOSALS</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">If you wish to submit a proposal for possible
inclusion in our proxy statement relating to our 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, send the proposal, by registered, certified,
or express mail to:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center">Gordon Y. Allison, Vice President and General
Counsel,<BR>
Corporate Division<BR>
Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.<BR>
702 Southwest 8<SUP>th </SUP>Street<BR>
Bentonville, Arkansas 72716-0215</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Shareholder proposals intended for inclusion
in our proxy statement for the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting in accordance with the SEC&rsquo;s Rule 14a-8 under the
Exchange Act must be received by our company in the manner described above no later than the close of business on December 24,
2014. Any shareholder proposal received by the company after that date will not be included in the company&rsquo;s proxy statement
relating to the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Further, all proposals submitted for inclusion in the company&rsquo;s
proxy statement relating to the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting must comply with all of the requirements of SEC Rule 14a-8.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Shareholders who wish to bring business
before Walmart&rsquo;s 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting other than through a shareholder proposal pursuant to the SEC&rsquo;s
rules must notify the Corporate Secretary of our company in writing and provide the information required by the provision of the
Bylaws dealing with business at annual and special meetings. Under the Bylaws, the notice must be delivered to or mailed and received
at Walmart&rsquo;s principal executive offices not less than 75 nor more than 100 days prior to the one-year anniversary of the
2014 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, unless the date of the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting is more than 30 days before
or more than 60 days after such anniversary date, in which case such notice must be delivered to or mailed and received at Walmart&rsquo;s
principal executive offices not more than 100 days prior to the date of the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting nor less than
the later of 75 days prior to the date of the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting or the tenth day following the day on which
a public announcement of the 2015 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting is made. The requirements for such notice are set forth in
the Bylaws, a copy of which can be found on our corporate website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com/corporate-governance/governance-documents.
</I>In addition, the Bylaws were filed with the SEC as Exhibit 3.1 to our company&rsquo;s Current Report on Form 8-K filed on
February 13, 2014. The Board periodically reviews the Bylaws, as in effect from time to time, and approves amendments as it deems
appropriate. Any amendments to the Bylaws will be reported in a filing with the SEC, as required by Form 8-K, and the amended
Bylaws will be filed as an exhibit to an SEC filing and posted on our corporate website at the web address above.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

President and CEO, Walmart&rsquo;s CFO, the next three most highly compensated Executive Officers other than our CEO and CFO during
fiscal 2014, and the Executive Vice President, President and CEO, Sam&rsquo;s Club during fiscal 2014, whom Walmart is voluntarily

<P STYLE="font: 22pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B><A NAME="lwmta053"></A>ANNEX A</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 19pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B>Non-GAAP Financial Measures</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">Certain financial measures we discussed in
the proxy statement under &ldquo;Executive Compensation&mdash;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&mdash;Fiscal 2014 Financial
Performance&rdquo; are considered non-GAAP financial measures under the SEC&rsquo;s rules because they are calculated by excluding
or including amounts that would be included or excluded in the calculation of comparable measures calculated in accordance with
GAAP. Below, we identify:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">those non-GAAP financial measures (the &ldquo;Non-GAAP Measures&rdquo;) and tell you briefly how we compute them; </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the financial measure calculated in accordance with GAAP or using only measures calculated in accordance with GAAP that we believe is the most directly comparable such financial measure to each Non-GAAP Measure (each, a &ldquo;Comparable GAAP Measure&rdquo;);</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 99%; border-collapse: collapse">
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="width: 10pt; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">the reasons why we think the Non-GAAP Measures provide our shareholders with useful information about our financial condition and results of operations; and </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
    <TD STYLE="padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; color: #0066CC">&bull;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-top: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">a reconciliation of each Non-GAAP Measure with its Comparable GAAP Measure.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">When we refer below to a financial measure
as being a &ldquo;reported&rdquo; financial measure, we are referring to a GAAP financial measure that was presented in our consolidated
statement of income for fiscal 2014 or fiscal 2013.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 15pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B>Constant Currency</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">We use currency exchange rates to convert
the operating results for all countries where the functional currency is not the U.S. dollar into U.S. dollars for financial reporting
purposes. A constant currency measure is one in which an item, such as operating income, for the current period is calculated by
using the comparable prior year period&rsquo;s currency exchange rates.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Non-GAAP Measures:</I> The company&rsquo;s
consolidated net sales for fiscal 2014 calculated without the impact of currency exchange rate fluctuations and without the impact
of acquisitions until the acquisitions are included in both comparable periods; the increase in the company&rsquo;s consolidated
net sales for fiscal 2014 without the impact of currency exchange rate fluctuations and acquisitions over reported consolidated
net sales for fiscal 2013; the increase in the net sales of our Walmart International operating segment for fiscal 2014 calculated
without the impact of currency exchange rate fluctuations and without the impact of acquisitions until the acquisitions are included
in both comparable periods over the reported net sales of that operating segment for fiscal 2013.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Comparable GAAP Measures:</I> Our reported
consolidated and International segment net sales for fiscal 2014 and the increases in our reported consolidated and International
segment net sales over fiscal 2013, respectively.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Why the Measures Are Useful Information:
</I>These constant currency financial measures permit investors to understand better Walmart&rsquo;s and the Walmart International
segment&rsquo;s core performance in fiscal 2014 without the effects of fluctuations in currency exchange rates, which are subject
to volatility from period to period, and the impact of acquisitions for fiscal 2014, compared to its performance in fiscal 2013.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Reconciliations:</I> Reconciliation of
the Non-GAAP Measures above to their respective Comparable GAAP Measures.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99%; font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif">

    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">$</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">477,457</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">$</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">11,853</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; border-bottom: Black 2px solid">2.5</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: left; border-bottom: Black 2px solid; padding-right: 2pt">%</TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>92</B></p>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 92 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Silver 4px solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 12pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 10pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%"><A HREF="#toc">Back to Contents</A></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"><PAGE></PAGE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B>Sam&rsquo;s Club Segment&rsquo;s
Net Sales and Operating Income, Excluding Fuel</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Non-GAAP Measures:</I> The increase in
our Sam&rsquo;s Club segment&rsquo;s net sales for fiscal 2014 over the segment&rsquo;s net sales for fiscal 2013, in each case
calculated by excluding fuel sales from each fiscal year&rsquo;s reported net sales of the segment; the increase in the segment&rsquo;s
operating income for fiscal 2014 over the segment&rsquo;s operating income for fiscal 2013, in each case calculated by excluding
the effect of fuel sales from the reported operating income of the segment for each fiscal year.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Comparable GAAP Measures:</I> The increase
in the segment&rsquo;s reported net sales and operating income for fiscal 2014 over the segment&rsquo;s reported net sales and
operating income for fiscal 2013, respectively.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Why the Measures Are Useful Information:
</I>The information permits investors to understand the effect of the fuel sales of our Sam&rsquo;s Club segment, which are affected
by the volatility of fuel prices, on the segment&rsquo;s net sales and operating income.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify"><I>Reconciliations:</I> Reconciliation of
the Non-GAAP Measures above to their respective Comparable GAAP Measures.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 20pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 12pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC"><B>Return on Investment</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify; color: #0066CC">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">We discuss our return on investment (&ldquo;ROI&rdquo;)
for fiscal year 2014 and include information about how we calculate that Non-GAAP Measure, its Comparable GAAP Measure, which
is our return on assets, and why that Non-GAAP Measure is useful information and provide a reconciliation of the two measures
in our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended January 31, 2014, which was filed with the SEC on March 21, 2014, and is
available on our investor relations website at <I>http://stock.walmart.com</I> and on the SEC&rsquo;s EDGAR system on its website
at <I>www.sec.gov.</I> That information appears in Exhibit 13 to that report under the caption &ldquo;Management&rsquo;s Discussion
and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&mdash;Company Performance Metrics&mdash;Returns&mdash;Return on
Investment.&rdquo;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">We define ROI as adjusted operating income
(operating income from continuing operations plus interest income, depreciation and amortization, and rent) for the fiscal year
divided by average investment during that period. We consider average investment to be the average of our beginning and ending
total assets of continuing operations plus average accumulated depreciation and amortization less average accounts payable and
average accrued liabilities for that fiscal year, plus a rent factor equal to the rent for the fiscal year multiplied by a factor
of eight.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: right"><IMG SRC="lwmt_footer.jpg" ALT="" STYLE="vertical-align:
top; width: 64px; height: 21px">&nbsp;<I>2014&nbsp;Proxy Statement</I>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>93</B></p>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 8pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">The use of cameras, camcorders, videotaping
equipment, and other recording devices will not be permitted in Bud Walton Arena. Attendees may not bring into the arena large
packages or other material that could pose a safety or disruption hazard (e.g., fireworks, noisemakers, horns, confetti, etc.).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 9pt Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0pt 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>
